SUMMARY:Continuous Identity in Practice Workshop (PDT)
DESCRIPTION:What does it actually take to build a modern IAM ecosystem?\nMo
 ving beyond the marketing hype\, this workshop will provide a real-world l
 ook at the journey to modern identity. We will break down the full lifecyc
 le\, sharing scars and successes—from the initial business case and stra
 tegy to the executive or boardroom pitch\, technical deployment\, and cont
 inuous evolution.\nWe’ll share lessons learned while "decoding" the crit
 ical components of aligning business stakeholders with requirements and mo
 dern architecture\, including: How to handle legacy debt while building fo
 r the future. How the path to better security is paved with tangible cost 
 savings and architectural rationalization. How a well-executed move isn't 
 just a security play\, it’s a financial one. How access\, provisioning\,
  and authorization are interrelated and crucial for streamlining and simpl
 ifying traditional "admin-time" IAM domains like IGA and PAM.\nThis is a h
 ands-on session designed to bridge the gap between business objectives and
  technical reality\, giving you the tools to lead your own successful IAM 
 modernization. Whether you are mid-migration or just embarking on this jou
 rney\, you will leave with a practical blueprint for transforming identity
  into a powerful business enabler.\n\nDetails: https://identiverse.com/idv
 26/continuous-identity-workshop/\n\nSpeakers: Andrew Cameron (Distinguishe
 d Engineer\, IAM • GM) | Sean O'Dell (Distinguished Engineer\, Identity 
 & Security • CVS Health)\n\nSession Type: WORKSHOP\n\nAll times are in P
 acific Daylight Time (PDT / UTC-7)
LOCATION:Mandalay Bay K
CLASS:PUBLIC
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:OPAQUE
