SUMMARY:Innovation Workshop - Kantara Initiative Offers Window of Opportuni
 ty (PDT)
DESCRIPTION:The Kantara Initiative focuses on innovation in the digital ide
 ntity marketplace to enhance privacy and security\, especially in the prot
 ection of personal data. This workshop will showcase how Kantara's work gr
 oups are solving burning issues arising in digital identity and engaging w
 ith stakeholders\, including relying parties and users\, in problem-solvin
 g and development of resources to make a difference. Kantara has five new 
 workgroups rolling out in 2026. Topics to be tackled include: Shadow AI in
  the Workplace\, Blinding Identity Taxonomy\, Digital Identity Risk Univer
 se\, Biometric Data\, Trusted Transaction Assurance\, and others\, alongsi
 de existing work groups on Privacy-Enhancing Mobile Credentials\, Anchored
  Notice and Consent Receipt\, User Managed Access\, and Resilient Identifi
 ers for Under-served Populations. More opportunities for new workgroups wi
 ll be announced before the conference. This is the chance to learn about t
 hese work areas and volunteer to lead efforts to solve the issues confront
 ing today's digital identity workplace.\n\nDetails: https://identiverse.co
 m/idv26/session/?idvid=3931715\n\nSpeakers: Kay Chopard (Executive Directo
 r • Kantara Initiative and Women in Identity)\n\nSession Type: MASTERCLA
 SS\n\nAll times are in Pacific Daylight Time (PDT / UTC-7)
LOCATION:Mandalay Bay H
