SUMMARY:Toward a Zero Trust Architecture for Agent Identities (PDT)
DESCRIPTION:Agents are exploding onto the Identity and Access Management sc
 ene. Fortune 1000 companies are experiencing an average of 10\,000 new age
 nt IDs in their environment over the past year. Agents present new identit
 y and access challenges: They reason and act in non-deterministic ways\, m
 uch more than workload identities\, but they consume data and act much qui
 cker than user identities. Based on real world conversations with enterpri
 se customers\, the Microsoft Customer Engineering team for Identity is pre
 senting an approach of how to apply Zero Trust principles in a practical w
 ay\, with a journey roadmap\, to agentic identities.\n\nDetails: https://i
 dentiverse.com/idv26/session/?idvid=3931750\n\nSpeakers: Tarek Dawoud (Pri
 ncipal Product Manager - Lead Architect • Microsoft)\n\nSession Type: MA
 STERCLASS\n\nAll times are in Pacific Daylight Time (PDT / UTC-7)
LOCATION:Breakers J
CLASS:PUBLIC
