SUMMARY:NIST Update on its Mobile Driver's License (mDL) Industry Partnersh
 ip (PDT)
DESCRIPTION:NIST's National Cybersecurity Center of Excellence (NCCoE) laun
 ched an initiative two years ago to partner with firms in banking\, health
 \, and tech to accelerate the adoption of standards and best practices for
  mobile driver’s licenses (mDLs). As phase one of that project wraps up 
 - and NIST publishes a new practice guide for use of mDLs in financial ser
 vices - this session will dive into the new practice guide\, and also talk
  about what comes next in future phases of the project focused on health c
 are and government services.\n\nDetails: https://identiverse.com/idv26/ses
 sion/?idvid=4033313\n\nSpeakers: Jeremy Grant (Coordinator • Better Iden
 tity Coalition) | William Fisher (Security Engineer • NIST) | Stefan Sch
 ubert (Managing Director • JP Morgan Chase) | Cisa Kurian (Principal Sec
 urity Advisor • CVS Health)\n\nSession Type: MASTERCLASS\n\nAll times ar
 e in Pacific Daylight Time (PDT / UTC-7)
LOCATION:Breakers L
CLASS:PUBLIC
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:OPAQUE
