SUMMARY:Debugging Passkeys for Professionals (PDT)
DESCRIPTION:In this advanced technical session Shane will take a develper-c
 entric look at open source tools he has built\, shared and used over the l
 ast few years of being a passkey practioner. He will cover common debuggin
 g scenarios for passkey deployments including what happens when attestatio
 n goes wrong\, how to decompose and interpret message payloads between bro
 wsers and servers\, and even investigating CTAP messages within the Chrome
  browser. Live demonstrations covering real support scenarios will be used
  to illustrate the value of these tools and show how root cause was determ
 ined. If you are a developer or technical support person assisting with pa
 sskey-related end user issues\, this session is sure to be of interest to 
 you!\n\nDetails: https://identiverse.com/idv26/session/?idvid=3931717\n\nS
 peakers: Shane Weeden (Senior Technical Staff Member • IBM)\n\nSession T
 ype: MASTERCLASS\n\nAll times are in Pacific Daylight Time (PDT / UTC-7)
LOCATION:Breakers H
