SUMMARY:Introduction to Privacy (PDT)
DESCRIPTION:Identity and privacy are inextricably intertwined\; strong iden
 tity supports privacy protection by mitigating risks of unauthorized acces
 s to personal data. At the same time\, the activities involved in establis
 hing strong identity involve the processing of individuals' information an
 d can therefore create privacy risks. This masterclass session provides at
 tendees with essential privacy basics including an overview of why privacy
  matters particularly in identity as well as fundamentals such as definiti
 ons of personal data\, an overview of the global regulatory landscape\, pr
 ivacy principles and values in action replete with practical examples from
  our presenters' collective industry and government experience. We’ll al
 so highlight privacy themes stemming from hot topics such as age verificat
 ion\, facial recognition\, and artificial intelligence.\n\nDetails: https:
 //identiverse.com/idv26/session/?idvid=3931722\n\nSpeakers: Zack Martin (D
 irector of Cybersecurity Services • Venable LLP) | Jamie Danker (Directo
 r\, Cloud Privacy Operations • Google)\n\nSession Type: MASTERCLASS\n\nA
 ll times are in Pacific Daylight Time (PDT / UTC-7)
