SUMMARY:Clinical Enterprise Authentication Simplified and Enhanced (PDT)
DESCRIPTION:NewYork-Presbyterian is redefining how our workforce accesses d
 igital systems through a unified passwordless authentication framework tha
 t combines speed\, security\, and ease of use. In partnership with Impriva
 ta and TwoSense\, this initiative extends the same passwordless capabiliti
 es introduced to non-clinical staff in November 2024 to the clinical enter
 prise. The result is an authentication experience that eliminates login fr
 iction\, maintains familiar workflows\, and strengthens identity assurance
 \; enhancing both operational efficiency and patient safety.\nClinical EAS
 E Highlights\nSeamless Integration: No change to how clinicians use the sy
 stems they need. Zero-Touch Enrollment: Transparent passwordless enablemen
 t requires no user setup or intervention.\nAdaptive Trust: Low-confidence 
 authentications automatically revert to existing Imprivata password replay
  mechanisms\, preserving uninterrupted access.\nFuture-Ready: Establishes 
 the foundation for behavior-based attestation in high-sensitivity clinical
  workflows.\nContinuous Identity Assurance: A lightweight endpoint agent p
 rovides identity verification and ongoing multifactor authentication. Enha
 nced Auditability: Each authentication event maps to a verified identity\,
  producing cleaner audit data.\n\nDetails: https://identiverse.com/idv26/s
 ession/?idvid=3931796\n\nSpeakers: Paul Smith (Directory - Identity Servic
 es • NewYork-Presbyterian) | Joe Neuman (Senior Technical Architec • N
 ewYork-Presbyterian)\n\nSession Type: MASTERCLASS\n\nAll times are in Paci
 fic Daylight Time (PDT / UTC-7)
LOCATION:Mandalay Bay D
