BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:identiverse-2026-event-4067443@identiverse.com
SEQUENCE:0
DTSTAMP:20260612T220134Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260615T190000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260615T191500
SUMMARY:Tech Theater Presented by Silverfort: Your Most Privileged Users Ar
 en’t People\, and What You Can Do About It (PDT)
DESCRIPTION:Privileged access used to be a human problem. But the most powe
 rful identities in today’s enterprise aren’t people. They’re service
  accounts\, APIs\, machine identities\, and AI agents operating at a scale
  and speed traditional PAM was never built for.\nMost PAM programs don’t
  stall because of a lack of tools. They stall because of people and proces
 s. Change management overhead and brittle workflows create so much frictio
 n that users find workarounds. Sound familiar?\nIn this session\, Rob Ains
 cough cuts through the theory and focuses on what actually works. Drawing 
 from real-world experience running IAM at a large UK retailer\, he’ll wa
 lk through practical patterns for securing privileged access across humans
 \, machines\, legacy systems\, cloud\, and AI without grinding the busines
 s to a halt. You’ll learn when vaults and session controls help\, when t
 hey hurt\, and how just-in-time approaches can remove standing privilege\,
  limit lateral movement\, and scale without breaking workflows.\nYou’ll 
 leave with clear takeaways\, fewer abstractions\, and a practical way to u
 se executive anxiety around AI constructively to drive alignment\, funding
 \, and momentum for PAM programs—positioning modern privileged access as
  a business enabler\, not another security tax.\n\nDetails: https://identi
 verse.com/idv26/session/?idvid=4067443\n\nSession Type: TECH THEATER\n\nAl
 l times are in Pacific Daylight Time (PDT / UTC-7)
LOCATION:Tech Theater 2
CLASS:PUBLIC
