BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:identiverse-2026-event-4187971@identiverse.com
SEQUENCE:0
DTSTAMP:20260612T220134Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260615T191000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260615T192500
SUMMARY:NHAI Pavilion Presented by Aizome: Not all AI Agents are Born Equal
  (PDT)
DESCRIPTION:In this first ever aizome session at Identiverse\, Amir Ofek\, 
 CEO and Co-founder of aizome\, will explore why the current traditional hu
 man IAM and NHI models are insufficient\, for the new Enterprise AI Agents
 . The session will cover the different type of agents existing today and t
 he associated identity traits of each. Unlike development or in-product ag
 ents\, Enterprise AI Agents are built within workforce business processes\
 , operating dynamically across diverse systems and requiring unique identi
 ty management\, and intent analysis. Because their roles are not fixed and
  their identities are often ambiguous\, they require a fundamentally diffe
 rent approach to security and management. Participants will examine the sh
 ift from Machine to Machine (M2M) to Agent to Agent (A2A) interaction\, wh
 ere identity is passed through complex chains and the original actor may b
 e completely abstracted. Amir will introduce a new model for maintaining a
  control based on real-time observation at the point of the AI agents' ope
 ration\, a hybrid identity that evolves with intent\, and dynamic controls
  driven by continuous behavioral analysis. Attendees will learn how to ena
 ble safe\, cross-systems AI operations through reusable connections rather
  than restrictive over-scoping ensuring that autonomous AI agents in Finan
 ce\, HR\, Marketing\, Sales\, Operations\, IT and beyond drive value and a
 ct within expected boundaries\n\nDetails: https://identiverse.com/idv26/se
 ssion/?idvid=4187971\n\nSession Type: NON-HUMAN & AI IDENTITY PAVILION\n\n
 All times are in Pacific Daylight Time (PDT / UTC-7)
LOCATION:NHAI Pavilion Theater
CLASS:PUBLIC
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:OPAQUE
