SUMMARY:Tech Theater Presented by Ping Identity: Stop Storing Biometric Dat
 a (PDT)
DESCRIPTION:This session will explore how Zero-Knowledge Biometric technolo
 gy enables server-side facial authentication without ever storing biometri
 c templates in retrievable or reconstructible form. We’ll unpack archite
 cture\, liveness and anti-injection controls\, and how to integrate privac
 y-preserving biometrics into real-world customer and workforce identity fl
 ows.\n3 Takeaways:\nHow to get biometric‑level assurance without storing
  biometric templates\, using device\, network\, and behavioral risk signal
 s from zero-knowledge biometrics.\nA reference implementation you can copy
 \, showing how to wire Recognize into your existing sign-on and step‑up 
 flows in minutes.\nA practical path to lower fraud and liability\, by remo
 ving stored biometric data from your environment while improving user expe
 rience.\n\nDetails: https://identiverse.com/idv26/session/?idvid=4145684\n
 \nSession Type: TECH THEATER\n\nAll times are in Pacific Daylight Time (PD
 T / UTC-7)
