SUMMARY:NHAI Pavilion Panel: Who Owns an Agentic AI Identity? (PDT)
DESCRIPTION:As AI agents begin to act autonomously\, making decisions\, inv
 oking tools\, and interacting with other systems\, traditional identity ow
 nership models start to break down. This session examines who should issue
 \, control\, and revoke agentic AI identities across technical\, legal\, a
 nd governance dimensions. Through concrete scenarios\, we’ll explore acc
 ountability\, liability\, and trust when agents act on behalf of humans\, 
 organizations\, or other agents. Attendees will leave with a framework for
  thinking about AI identity ownership before policy and architecture decis
 ions lock them in.\n\nDetails: https://identiverse.com/idv26/session/?idvi
 d=4216663\n\nSession Type: NON-HUMAN & AI IDENTITY PAVILION\n\nAll times a
 re in Pacific Daylight Time (PDT / UTC-7)
