BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:identiverse-2026-event-3931703@identiverse.com
SEQUENCE:0
DTSTAMP:20260612T220134Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260616T103000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260616T105500
SUMMARY:Lies\, Damned Lies\, and Privacy (PDT)
DESCRIPTION:Privacy has all but disappeared -- not through breaches\, but c
 ountless design choices. Our phones\, networks\, browsers\, digital wallet
 s\, mobile driver's licenses\, and credentials all promise access\, securi
 ty\, and convenience. They also leave traces that make our lives correlata
 ble and controllable.\nFunctional anonymity is dying\, but anonymity alone
  is not the solution. We must identify ourselves to access services\, prev
 ent fraud\, and participate in society. Many of our rights depend upon ide
 ntification - rights which paradoxically include the right to privacy.\nTh
 is talk explores the challenges\, tensions\, and trade-offs that constrain
  privacy. It asks what technologies and standards can help us chart a path
  toward digital agency.\n\nDetails: https://identiverse.com/idv26/session/
 ?idvid=3931703\n\nSpeakers: Elizabeth Garber (Executive Director • IDPro
 )\n\nSession Type: SESSION\n\nAll times are in Pacific Daylight Time (PDT 
 / UTC-7)
LOCATION:Mandalay Bay F
