BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:identiverse-2026-event-4067369@identiverse.com
SEQUENCE:0
DTSTAMP:20260612T220134Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260616T103000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260616T105500
SUMMARY:Identity for AI Agents: Passkeys\, Delegation and Human Authorizati
 on (PDT)
DESCRIPTION:AI agents are rapidly becoming first-class actors inside enterp
 rise systems\, but most identity architectures still assume humans at the 
 keyboard. This session looks at what it means to give an AI agent a real i
 dentity and the resulting impact on authentication\, authorization and tru
 st delegation.\nWe explore how AI agents can be issued passkeys and verifi
 able credentials and how organizations can ensure agents are genuinely act
 ing on behalf of authenticated humans. We walkthrough real-world operating
  models:\nAutonomous executionHuman-in-the-loopException-based oversightWe
  show how agent identity can be cryptographically bound to users while rem
 aining auditable and governed.\nThe session also addresses when an agent m
 ay act independently and when it must request step-up authorization. This 
 is tied into emerging regulation (e.g.\, EU AI Act\, NY RAISE Act) and its
  impact on traceability and intent verification.\nWe close with practical 
 enterprise architectures for agent trust in a passwordless world\, grounde
 d in WebAuthn\, scoped delegation and explicit human approval for high-imp
 act actions.\nAttendees will leave with a clear framework for deploying AI
  agents safely\, without sacrificing security\, compliance or user trust.\
 nSession Presented by:\n\nDetails: https://identiverse.com/idv26/session/?
 idvid=4067369\n\nSpeakers: Bojan Simic (CEO • HYPR)\n\nSession Type: SES
 SION\n\nAll times are in Pacific Daylight Time (PDT / UTC-7)
LOCATION:Breakers J
