DTSTAMP:20260612T220134Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260616T110500
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260616T113000
SUMMARY:Harvest Now\, Break Later: The Quantum Threat to Digital Identity (
 PDT)
DESCRIPTION:Quantum computing won’t just disrupt encryption. It will quie
 tly invalidate today’s identity trust model. Attackers are already colle
 cting encrypted identity data with the expectation that quantum systems wi
 ll break it later.\nThis session challenges a dangerous assumption: that i
 dentity cryptography is “someone else’s problem.” We’ll explain wh
 y RSA and elliptic-curve algorithms underpinning SSO\, certificates\, toke
 ns and machine identities will fail\, what post-quantum alternatives actua
 lly exist\, and why waiting for vendors is the riskiest option.\nThis talk
  isn’t about math. It’s about timing\, responsibility\, and trust. If 
 identity teams don’t start inventorying cryptographic dependencies and p
 lanning transitions now\, they’ll inherit tomorrow’s breach even years
  after the data was stolen.\n\nDetails: https://identiverse.com/idv26/sess
 ion/?idvid=3931674\n\nSpeakers: Jesse Minor (Identity Security Specialist 
 • KPMG)\n\nSession Type: SESSION\n\nAll times are in Pacific Daylight Ti
 me (PDT / UTC-7)
LOCATION:Mandalay Bay K
CLASS:PUBLIC
STATUS:CONFIRMED
