BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:identiverse-2026-event-3931810@identiverse.com
SEQUENCE:0
DTSTAMP:20260612T220134Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260616T110500
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260616T113000
SUMMARY:IAM for AI: From "Eh\, I?" to "I am." (PDT)
DESCRIPTION:Comparable only to seismic shifts like the Industrial Revolutio
 n or the rise of the Internet\, the emergence of artificial intelligence i
 s unquestionably transformative. But does it really demand an equally radi
 cal upheaval in IAM standards and technology? With the seemingly endless p
 arade of prophets and profiteers declaring the revolution imminent and ass
 uring us that they alone can lead it\, you might think so.\nThe reality mi
 ght be less dramatic and more practical. Many of the core challenges of 'I
 AM for AI' look pretty familiar. Regular old OAuth is already well suited 
 to a surprising amount of AI systems' needs\, and emerging efforts like CI
 MD and ID-JAG seem poised to fill in some of the gaps. It may be that our 
 existing IAM foundation can rise to the occasion\, or that our expectation
 s can be tempered to meet the moment.\nJoin a curmudgeonly pragmatist and 
 occasional Identiverse contributor on a journey from 'Eh\, I?' to 'I am.' 
 without inciting revolution.\n\nDetails: https://identiverse.com/idv26/ses
 sion/?idvid=3931810\n\nSpeakers: Brian Campbell (Distinguished Engineer 
 • Ping Identity)\n\nSession Type: SESSION\n\nAll times are in Pacific Da
 ylight Time (PDT / UTC-7)
LOCATION:Mandalay Bay I
CLASS:PUBLIC
