BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:identiverse-2026-event-3931776@identiverse.com
SEQUENCE:0
DTSTAMP:20260612T220134Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260616T110500
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260616T113000
SUMMARY:"I Have a Feeling We're Not in Kansas Anymore": What Makes Agentic 
 AI Identity So Different? (PDT)
DESCRIPTION:Historically\, "identity" has been defined by the relative stab
 ility of the thing identified.\nHuman identity centers on a persistent set
  of relatively invariable characteristics. Even traditional software appli
 cation identity relies on static\, predictable service accounts executing 
 linear\, pre-programmed logic that changes infrequently.\nHowever\, as we 
 follow the yellow brick road into the era of agentic AI\, we must look beh
 ind the curtain to see how the wizard really works\, in order to understan
 d its identity (or identities).\nAgentic AI identity is fundamentally diff
 erent because it is defined not by a fixed configuration\, but by dynamic 
 agency. The autonomous ability to reason\, plan\, and mutate its own execu
 tion path in real-time\, and the injection of natural-language prompts by 
 humans\, that must be parsed and translated into running code.\nThis sessi
 on will explore how this shift from reactive automation to autonomous init
 iative creates a new "identity blur\," where the software's "identity" is 
 as ephemeral and context-dependent as the natural language and non-determi
 nistic robot agency that created it.\nWith the courage of a lion\, a heart
  big enough that only a tin man can have\, and with a click of the heels o
 f our ruby slippers\, we'll take a peek behind the curtain at the challeng
 es of agentic identity\, and how we might tackle them.\n\nDetails: https:/
 /identiverse.com/idv26/session/?idvid=3931776\n\nSpeakers: John Kemp (Seni
 or Manager\, Identity Security Management • Capital One)\n\nSession Type
 : SESSION\n\nAll times are in Pacific Daylight Time (PDT / UTC-7)
LOCATION:Mandalay Bay H
