BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:identiverse-2026-event-4056119@identiverse.com
SEQUENCE:0
DTSTAMP:20260612T220134Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260616T110500
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260616T113000
SUMMARY:The Identity Gap: Proof of Humanity in an Agentic World (PDT)
DESCRIPTION:Passkeys are powerful and have vastly improved enterprise authe
 ntication.\nBut some of the most important identity moments happen when th
 ey aren’t available.\nBefore a new hire has a device. During onboarding 
 and recovery. In shared environments. And when AI agents act on a person
 ’s behalf.\nIn those moments\, organisations still need trust\, accounta
 bility\, and proof that a real human — and the right human — is behind
  the action.\nWhile passkeys secure the device\, they don’t always secur
 e intent.\nThis session moves beyond the login to explore the technical ar
 chitecture of proof ofhumanity. We will break down how to maintain a chain
  of trust across key identity lifecycle stages — from onboarding\, login
 \, and recovery to agent-driven actions — ensuring that even when a pass
 key is absent\, accountability remains.\nBecause in the agentic era\, iden
 tity isn’t just about login. It’s about knowing which human is behind 
 the action — and that they are the right one.\nSession Presented by:\n\n
 Details: https://identiverse.com/idv26/session/?idvid=4056119\n\nSpeakers:
  Andrew Bud (CEO & Founder • iProov)\n\nSession Type: SESSION\n\nAll tim
 es are in Pacific Daylight Time (PDT / UTC-7)
