SUMMARY:Cursor for IAM: Reimagining Identity Governance Through AI-Driven D
 esign (PDT)
DESCRIPTION:Identity Governance programs have long relied on heavy customiz
 ation\, complex configurations\, and frequent redesign—placing a sustain
 ed burden on IAM teams. This session introduces AI-powered IGA Design Stud
 io\, a modern approach that enables practitioners to convert business inte
 nt directly into governed\, reusable identity artifacts across joiner/move
 r/leaver processes\, access reviews\, policies\, and integrations.\nAttend
 ees will learn how AI-assisted design\, validation\, and deployment can si
 gnificantly reduce manual effort while maintaining strong auditability\, g
 overnance controls\, and alignment with vendor-specific requirements. The 
 session will also highlight real-world scenarios such as redesigning exist
 ing configurations\, reusing proven models\, and migrating identity setups
 —areas traditionally known for their complexity and time intensity.\nWe
 ’ll close with a forward-looking perspective on how AI is redefining the
  role of IAM professionals\, shifting them from configuration-focused exec
 ution to higher-value governance architecture and decision-making.\n\nDeta
 ils: https://identiverse.com/idv26/session/?idvid=4142010\n\nSpeakers: San
 jay Nadimpalli (CEO • Tuebora)\n\nSession Type: SESSION\n\nAll times are
  in Pacific Daylight Time (PDT / UTC-7)
