BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:identiverse-2026-event-4172909@identiverse.com
SEQUENCE:0
DTSTAMP:20260612T220134Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260616T110500
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260616T113000
SUMMARY:Agentic AI Is Here: Industry Analyst Insights\, FIDO Standards & Wh
 at’s Next (PDT)
DESCRIPTION:Just as we’ve grown comfortable securing humans and devices\,
  a new actor has entered the system: autonomous agents that act\, decide\,
  and transact.\nThe rise of agentic AI didn’t begin in the enterprise\, 
 it began with the consumer. Just as ChatGPT reshaped expectations\, person
 al AI agents are now managing digital lives and increasingly interacting w
 ith enterprise systems. These agents aren’t coming\, they’re already h
 ere\, knocking on the front door of your identity stack.\nWhat does this m
 ean for customer identity? How do trust models evolve? And what new identi
 ty\, fraud\, and threat vectors emerge when agents become first-class acto
 rs?\nJoin David Mahdi - Transmit Security\, Andras Cser - Forrester\, and 
 Karen Larsen - FIDO Alliance\, as they bring together analyst insight and 
 standards leadership to explore how agentic AI is reshaping identity. This
  session will challenge legacy assumptions and provide a clear view of wha
 t security teams must do now to prepare for the next wave of identity disr
 uption.\nSession Presented by:\n\nDetails: https://identiverse.com/idv26/s
 ession/?idvid=4172909\n\nSpeakers: Karen Larson (Director of Product Manag
 ement and Operations • FIDO Alliance) | Andras Cser (Vice President\, Pr
 incipal Analyst • Forrester) | David Mahdi (CIO • Transmit Security)\n
 \nSession Type: SESSION\n\nAll times are in Pacific Daylight Time (PDT / U
 TC-7)
