UID:identiverse-2026-event-3931786@identiverse.com
SEQUENCE:0
DTSTAMP:20260612T220134Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260616T114000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260616T123000
SUMMARY:OMG PQC is Gonna Impact IAM - and it Might be AOK (PDT)
DESCRIPTION:Post Quantum Cryptography (PQC) is no longer just a theoretical
  concept - NIST has approved several PQC algorithms and the race is on to 
 update systems to use them in advance of the emergence of quantum computer
 s that will be able to compromise legacy cryptographic algorithms. But wha
 t does this mean for IAM? And how should product vendors and implementers 
 be planning to support these new tools? Come here from the head of NIST's 
 Cryptographic Technology Group - who is leading work on the PQC algorithms
  - along with key leaders from industry who are supporting the migration.\
 n\nDetails: https://identiverse.com/idv26/session/?idvid=3931786\n\nSpeake
 rs: Brian Campbell (Distinguished Engineer • Ping Identity) | Jeremy Gra
 nt (Coordinator • Better Identity Coalition) | Teresa Wu (Vice President
 \, Smart Credentials & Smart Integrate • IDEMIA Public Security) | Andre
 w Regenscheid (Manager\, Cryptographic Technology Group • NIST (National
  Institute of Standards and Technology))\n\nSession Type: MASTERCLASS\n\nA
 ll times are in Pacific Daylight Time (PDT / UTC-7)
LOCATION:Mandalay Bay K
CLASS:PUBLIC
