BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:identiverse-2026-event-4056114@identiverse.com
SEQUENCE:0
DTSTAMP:20260612T220134Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260616T114000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260616T123000
SUMMARY:The Fatal Silo: Why Separating Identity and Data Security Is Your N
 ext Breach Waiting to Happen (PDT)
DESCRIPTION:The perimeter has evolved—it is no longer confined to the net
 work edge but embedded within identity itself. Yet most organizations stil
 l treat Identity and Access Management and Data Security as separate domai
 ns\, operating in silos with distinct tools and strategies. This disconnec
 t creates a critical blind spot: “Shadow Access” to “Shadow Data\,
 ” without clear alignment to the data\, customer experiences\, and busin
 ess outcomes it is meant to protect.\nIn this session\, we confront the re
 ality that identity governance now directly impacts growth\, trust\, and r
 egulatory risk. Today’s breaches often begin not with intrusion\, but wi
 th attackers already inside—using valid credentials to access data organ
 izations didn’t know was exposed.\nWe will explore why the most dangerou
 s threat is the over-permissioned identity—human or non-human—with sea
 mless\, unmonitored access to sensitive data. We will also examine the int
 ersection of DSPM and ISPM\, and how to operationalize a Cybersecurity Mes
 h to build a context-aware security fabric.\nKey Takeaways:\nThe greatest 
 risk is over-permissioned access to sensitive data—not just unauthorized
  entry.\nSiloed Identity and Data Security increase regulatory\, financial
 \, and reputational exposure.\nOver-permissioned identities signal a syste
 mic control gap.\nLinking identity governance to data sensitivity is criti
 cal to protecting revenue and trust.\nSession Presented by:\n\nDetails: ht
 tps://identiverse.com/idv26/session/?idvid=4056114\n\nSpeakers: Ammar Fahe
 em (Director\, Product Marketing\, CIAM • Thales) | Jason Keenaghan (Dir
 ector of Product Management & UX Design\, IAM • Thales) | Joseph Miceli 
 (Distinguished Author – IAM Transformation and Growth Executive •) | J
 ohn Tolbert (Principal Analyst • KuppingerCole Analysts)\n\nSession Type
 : MASTERCLASS\n\nAll times are in Pacific Daylight Time (PDT / UTC-7)
LOCATION:Breakers L
