SUMMARY:NHAI Pavilion Panel: Zero Trust Meets Non-Human Identity: Still Val
 id or Already Broken? (PDT)
DESCRIPTION:Zero Trust assumes known identities\, defined perimeters\, and 
 predictable access patterns. Agentic AI breaks all three. This session exp
 lores whether Zero Trust principles still apply in a world of autonomous\,
  non-human actors\, or whether they need to be fundamentally reinterpreted
 . Attendees will gain a realistic view of which Zero Trust concepts hold u
 p\, which don’t\, and how security models may need to evolve for agent-d
 riven systems.\n\nDetails: https://identiverse.com/idv26/session/?idvid=42
 16665\n\nSession Type: NON-HUMAN & AI IDENTITY PAVILION\n\nAll times are i
