SUMMARY:Power Lunch Presented by CrowdStrike: Stopping Identity Attacks in 
 the AI Era: Real-World Lessons from CrowdStrike\, MGM Resorts\, and Penske
  Automotive (PDT)
DESCRIPTION:AI is changing the game for adversaries—automating reconnaiss
 ance\, scaling social engineering\, and accelerating lateral movement. But
  even the most advanced\, agentic attacks still rely on a familiar foundat
 ion: compromised identities. According to CrowdStrike threat intelligence\
 , today’s adversaries are operating with increasing speed and precision
 —leveraging valid accounts\, escalating privileges\, and blending into n
 ormal activity to evade detection across identity\, endpoint\, SaaS\, and 
 cloud. You’ll hear directly from security leaders at CrowdStrike\, MGM R
 esorts\, and Penske Automotive as they share how they’ve operationalized
  identity security to detect and stop these attacks in progress—before t
 hey become breaches. You'll walk away with practical approaches to operati
 onalize identity as a core security control.\n\nDetails: https://identiver
 se.com/idv26/session/?idvid=4134854\n\nSession Type: POWER LUNCH\n\nAll ti
 mes are in Pacific Daylight Time (PDT / UTC-7)
