SUMMARY:Power Lunch Presented by Veza from ServiceNow: Identity Security fo
 r the AI Era: Shifting from Identity Debt to Continuous Control (PDT)
DESCRIPTION:Adversaries aren't breaking in\, they're logging in. The Veza 2
 026 State of Identity & Access Report reveals 38% of accounts are dormant 
 with live entitlements\, and safe and compliant permissions are declining 
 sharply every year. And now\, AI agents are exacerbating this exposure wit
 h inconsistent identity implementations across platforms with limited visi
 bility. In this session\, let's move past the theory\, and explore how to 
 quantify identity debt\, close non-human and AI agent blind spots\, and sh
 ift to an authorization-focused security model. We will explore five concr
 ete strategies to harden your identity program for 2026.\n\nDetails: https
 ://identiverse.com/idv26/session/?idvid=4134857\n\nSession Type: POWER LUN
 CH\n\nAll times are in Pacific Daylight Time (PDT / UTC-7)
