SUMMARY:Tech Theater Presented by HID Global: The Data Is In: The Business 
 Case for Converged Identity (PDT)
DESCRIPTION:New joint research from HID and the FIDO Alliance\nDespite grow
 ing awareness of converged identity\, most enterprises have yet to priorit
 ize it as a strategic initiative — and those that have are encountering 
 significant deployment complexity. This session presents findings from new
  joint research conducted by HID and the FIDO Alliance\, examining how org
 anizations currently manage physical and digital identity\, where fragment
 ation is creating measurable security and operational risk\, and what the 
 data reveals about the conditions required to move converged identity from
  concept to execution. Attendees will leave with a data-backed framework f
 or building the business case for convergence within their organizations.W
 hat you'll learn:How enterprises currently structure physical and digital 
 identity governance — and where fragmentation is creating exploitable ga
 psWhat the research reveals about credential lifecycle failures: offboardi
 ng vulnerabilities\, orphaned access\, and untracked credential sprawlThe 
 deployment barriers preventing organizations from acting on converged iden
 tity — even when intent existsThe current state of FIDO2 and passkey ado
 ption across the enterprise\, and what it signals about convergence readin
 essWhat the data tells us about the business case for converged identity 
 — and what it would take to move it onto the strategic agenda\n\nDetails
 : https://identiverse.com/idv26/session/?idvid=4141509\n\nSession Type: TE
 CH THEATER\n\nAll times are in Pacific Daylight Time (PDT / UTC-7)
LOCATION:Tech Theater 2
