SUMMARY:Debunking ‘My Users Don’t Understand Passkeys’: How VicRoads 
 Went Passkey-First for 5 Million Users (PDT)
DESCRIPTION:Many large enterprises and government agencies are discussing h
 ow they can integrate passkeys into their product and services but fear th
 at they might overwhelm users and their passkey implementation will not be
  used.\nVicRoads has emerged as a pioneer in large-scale passkey adoption 
 in the public sector. This session will take attendees through VicRoads' j
 ourney - from initial research and requirements gathering to deployment an
 d mass user adoption.\nWith millions of users spanning diverse demographic
 s\, devices and technical backgrounds\, rolling out passkeys at this scale
  presented its unique challenges:\nMany users may have never heard of pass
 keys and how to use them\nVery heterogeneous devices\, OS and browser land
 scape that could potentially cause a very different UX\nYou can’t overwh
 elm your customer support center by introducing passkeys\nThis talk will h
 ighlight the key decisions made\, best practices identified and lessons le
 arned\, ensuring other organizations can confidently implement passkeys wh
 ile minimizing friction and maximizing adoption. Specifically we want to p
 rovide insights into:\nGet high passkey adoption: learn different strategi
 es and their impact on core KPIs\nAnalytics & login observability: interes
 ting patterns we found & how to process mine passkey logins\nReduce the ri
 sk when rolling out passkeys: gradual rollout\, exclude OS versions\, prov
 ide seamless fallbacks\, clear UX/UI and error handling\nThis session will
  provide details on how users have responded to passkeys\, adoption metric
 s and how VicRoads continues to optimize its implementation.\nAttendees wi
 ll gain actionable strategies on user onboarding\, managing edge cases\, r
 educing customer support burdens and achieving cost savings - essential in
 sights for any organization looking to deploy passkeys at scale.\nKey Take
 aways:\nStrategic lessons from a large-scale government deployment: Unders
 tand the planning\, challenges and success factors that enabled VicRoads t
 o roll out passkeys to a vast user base.\nUser-centric deployment & adopti
 on strategies: Learn best practices for introducing passkeys to diverse us
 ers\, avoiding user lockouts and handling device-specific edge cases.\nDri
 ving business impact: Discover how passkeys helped VicRoads reduce support
  tickets\, cut SMS costs and improve security - all while enhancing the us
 er experience.\nPost-launch optimization & continuous Improvement: See rea
 l-world adoption metrics\, user feedback and how ongoing optimizations hav
 e improved passkey usage rates over time.\nWhy this talk?\nOne of the larg
 est government passkey deployments worldwide: VicRoads’ experience provi
 des invaluable insights for other government agencies and enterprises plan
 ning large-scale implementations.\nReal-world adoption data & best practic
 es: Unlike theoretical discussions\, this session shares live deployment m
 etrics and hard-earned lessons to help organizations execute successfully.
 \nDirectly applicable insights: This talk is designed to equip attendees w
 ith clear\, actionable steps for deploying passkeys at scale with confiden
 ce.\n\nDetails: https://identiverse.com/idv26/session/?idvid=3931671\n\nSp
 eakers: Vincent Delitz (Managing Director • Corbado)\n\nSession Type: SE
 SSION\n\nAll times are in Pacific Daylight Time (PDT / UTC-7)
LOCATION:Mandalay Bay F
