SUMMARY:Verifiable Information: A Global Opportunity to Increase Trust and 
 Reduce Cost (PDT)
DESCRIPTION:Within the broader context of AI and the general digitization o
 f society\, we\, as nations and citizens\, are seeking to regain control o
 ver our data and digital interactions.\nIn this arena\, a new approach is 
 emerging globally\, driven by the emergence of cryptographically advanced 
 digital wallets.\nBy leveraging the asynchronous nature of wallet-centered
  data sharing\, we can now issue\, hold\, present\, and verify a wide rang
 e of information\, far beyond just the foundational identity we have mainl
 y discussed so far.\nOrganisations can issue information that makes sense 
 within their particular value chain. And as consumers of verifiable inform
 ation\, they can save significantly by avoiding the time\, labor\, and mon
 ey required to ensure that information is correct\, valid\, and trustworth
 y. Thereby\, everybody has less risk\, which will translate into improved 
 earnings for companies and/or lower prices for customers.\nThis talk will 
 explore how this comes about and what you can do to reap the commercial be
 nefits from the new wallet-centered information sharing opportunities.\n\n
 Details: https://identiverse.com/idv26/session/?idvid=3931656\n\nSpeakers:
  Niels Flensted-Jensen (CEO\, Co-founder • Idura)\n\nSession Type: SESSI
 ON\n\nAll times are in Pacific Daylight Time (PDT / UTC-7)
LOCATION:Mandalay Bay K
