SUMMARY:Identity Security Moves at the Speed of App Onboarding (PDT)
DESCRIPTION:Someone left your company three weeks ago. You revoked their SS
 O access in minutes. Deprovisioned their core systems. Disabled their VPN.
  Pulled their badge access. Clean exit.\nThen you get the Slack message: "
 Hey\, the ex-employee is still commenting in our project management tool. 
 Can you remove them?"\nYou check. They're still active in the analytics pl
 atform. Still have access to the collaboration tool. Still in the file sha
 ring app. Apps you knew existed but never got around to integrating. Apps 
 sitting at position 23\, 47\, and 61 in your backlog.\nThis is the real pr
 oblem. Not the apps you've integrated - those work fine. It's everything e
 lse. The apps accumulating faster than you can build connectors for them.\
 nThe standard playbook says: comprehensive integration or nothing. Full pr
 ovisioning\, complete attribute mapping\, perfect lifecycle management. So
  apps wait. And wait. While people use them anyway.\nThis session shows yo
 u a different path: baseline security first\, comprehensive integration la
 ter. Get SSO deployed. Establish a disable mechanism. Use whatever integra
 tion method works - APIs\, connectors\, workflows\, whatever gets the job 
 done.\nYou'll learn prioritization frameworks\, practical integration patt
 erns\, and how to actually close the gap.Note: This session does not promo
 te any product or service. It’s focused entirely on industry challenges 
 and practical best practices.\n\nDetails: https://identiverse.com/idv26/se
 ssion/?idvid=3931766\n\nSpeakers: Prithvi Poreddy (Head of IAM • Triumph
 )\n\nSession Type: SESSION\n\nAll times are in Pacific Daylight Time (PDT 
 / UTC-7)
LOCATION:Mandalay Bay H
