BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:identiverse-2026-event-4117129@identiverse.com
SEQUENCE:0
DTSTAMP:20260612T220134Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260616T140000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260616T142500
SUMMARY:Turn Rich Data into Your Identity Super Power with Continuous Ident
 ity (PDT)
DESCRIPTION:Your identity controls likely still rely on static\, standing p
 rivileges and rarely evaluate the operating context about why access is ne
 eded by a specific user or agent right now. This can leave your critical i
 nfrastructure vulnerable to threats\, especially in the age of AI and mach
 ine-speed attacks. We don't need fewer friction points\; we need more—mo
 re telemetry\, more context\, and more enforcement.\nThis session explores
  both the current and future benefits of adopting a Continuous Identity st
 rategy now\, discussing how fusing continuous identity evaluation with dee
 p device\, cloud\, and browser telemetry enables dynamic access controls t
 hroughout every identity process\, enforcing data-rich authorization check
 s across IDPs\, APIs\, MCP Gateways\, endpoints\, browser sessions and ind
 ividual transactions.\nAttendees will learn how to:\nReplace static privil
 eges by leveraging more security telemetry and more business context\, wit
 hout slowing the business.\nExpand enforcement across identity\, API\, end
 point\, and browser layers to increase friction for adversaries - not user
 s.\nBuild close-loop remediation workflows that automatically shrink acces
 s windows and stop threats in real time.\nLeverage emerging approaches - s
 uch as continuous\, context-aware authorization innovations enabled by Cro
 wdStrike’s acquisition of SGNL - to turn access from a one-time decision
  to a real-time control plane.\nSession Presented by:\n\nDetails: https://
 identiverse.com/idv26/session/?idvid=4117129\n\nSpeakers: Mat Hamlin (Dire
 ctor\, Product Management • CrowdStrike) | Faraz Jamal (Director of Prod
 uct for Identity Protection • CrowdStrike)\n\nSession Type: SESSION\n\nA
 ll times are in Pacific Daylight Time (PDT / UTC-7)
LOCATION:Mandalay Bay D
CLASS:PUBLIC
