BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:identiverse-2026-event-4122714@identiverse.com
SEQUENCE:0
DTSTAMP:20260612T220134Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260616T140000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260616T142500
SUMMARY:Man\, Machine\, and Malice: Securing the Full AI-Powered Developmen
 t Lifecycle (PDT)
DESCRIPTION:The software development lifecycle is being fundamentally trans
 formed by AI\, from AI-assisted coding to autonomous agents deploying infr
 astructure. This new paradigm introduces complex identity questions: How d
 o we trust the code from a human-AI pair? How do we manage the identities 
 of an autonomous agent workforce? Who is accountable when an AI goes rogue
 ?\nThis panel brings together leaders from the trenches of cloud infrastru
 cture and enterprise security to debate and discuss how to secure this new
  world from end to end. Featuring insights from Snowflake and Monolithic P
 ower Systems\, we will explore the practical challenges and solutions for 
 establishing identity\, observability\, and control in an AI-powered SDLC.
 \nThe discussion will cover the spectrum of the problem\, from verifying t
 he developer at the point of commit to managing the access rights of auton
 omous agents interacting with private data. Attendees will gain a multi-fa
 ceted perspective on the strategies and technologies needed to ensure that
  innovation in AI development does not come at the cost of security and tr
 ust.\nSession Presented by:\n\nDetails: https://identiverse.com/idv26/sess
 ion/?idvid=4122714\n\nSpeakers: Huy Ly (Head of IT Infrastructure / Securi
 ty • Monolithic Power Systems) | Gaurav Singodia (• Snowflake)\n\nSess
 ion Type: SESSION\n\nAll times are in Pacific Daylight Time (PDT / UTC-7)
LOCATION:Breakers H
