SUMMARY:Identity at OpenAI (PDT)
DESCRIPTION:At OpenAI\, we view identity security and privacy as foundation
 al requirements for agentic AI systems. This session explores how we are b
 eginning to think about agent identity\, the challenges that exist today\,
  and how these challenges may be addressed collaboratively through the ide
 ntity ecosystem and open standards. As AI systems increasingly act on beha
 lf of users\, we’ll examine the relationship between user and agent iden
 tity\, and how appropriate delegation\, accountability\, and control can b
 e achieved while preserving user privacy in both consumer and enterprise c
 ontexts.\n\nDetails: https://identiverse.com/idv26/session/?idvid=3931813\
 n\nSpeakers: Nick Steele (Member of Technical Staff • OpenAI)\n\nSession
  Type: SESSION\n\nAll times are in Pacific Daylight Time (PDT / UTC-7)
