BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:identiverse-2026-event-4082870@identiverse.com
SEQUENCE:0
DTSTAMP:20260612T220134Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260616T143500
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260616T150000
SUMMARY:From Humans to Agents: Rethinking Identity for Your Next Wave of Gr
 owth (PDT)
DESCRIPTION:The way users interact with applications is fundamentally chang
 ing. In the age of AI agents\, humans are no longer the primary interface\
 , software is.\nAs autonomous agents begin to search\, decide\, and act on
  behalf of users\, identity emerges as the crucial control plane for this 
 new agent economy. Yet\, most existing identity systems were not built to 
 handle non-human actors operating at scale.\nIn this session\, we’ll int
 roduce a new identity model in the agentic era\, one that unifies humans\,
  machines\, APIs\, and AI agents under a single\, extensible identity laye
 r. We’ll examine real-world scenarios like agent-driven commerce and ent
 erprise automation to illustrate what’s at stake if identity is not mode
 rnized.\nWhether you are an enterprise developer writing Java or GO\, or a
 n architect “vibe coding” with Replit or Lovable\, you will walk away 
 with a clear framework for transforming identity from a mere operational n
 ecessity into a competitive advantage\, securely scaling your creativity a
 nd business from your first human user to a full fleet of autonomous AI ag
 ents.\nSession Presented by:\n\nDetails: https://identiverse.com/idv26/ses
 sion/?idvid=4082870\n\nSpeakers: Abhishek Hingnikar (Product Architect II 
 • Okta) | Micah Spieler (Chief Product Office • Strike Graph)\n\nSessi
 on Type: SESSION\n\nAll times are in Pacific Daylight Time (PDT / UTC-7)
LOCATION:Mandalay Bay D
