SUMMARY:Unifying Identity and Network Access for the AI Era (PDT)
DESCRIPTION:AI is changing how access decisions are made. Identities now in
 clude users\, services\, workloads\, and AI agents operating at machine sp
 eed\, exposing gaps between identity and network controls. This session in
 troduces the Access Fabric as a unifying model that connects identity sign
 als with device\, data\, and network context to deliver consistent\, adapt
 ive access for any identity\, employee or AI. We will also explore how Mic
 rosoft is applying this Access Fabric internally\, including the security 
 and operational benefits achieved by unifying identity and network access.
 \nSession Presented by:\n\nDetails: https://identiverse.com/idv26/session/
 ?idvid=4056128\n\nSpeakers: Kaitlin Murphy (Senior Director\, Product Mark
 eting • Microsoft)\n\nSession Type: SESSION\n\nAll times are in Pacific 
 Daylight Time (PDT / UTC-7)
