BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:identiverse-2026-event-4076644@identiverse.com
SEQUENCE:0
DTSTAMP:20260612T220134Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260616T151000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260616T153500
SUMMARY:When AI Becomes the User: Rethinking CIAM for Agentic Clients (PDT)
DESCRIPTION:Consumers don’t always log in anymore\, their AI does. In a w
 orld where AI agents are supposed to be acting on behalf of our consumers\
 , we can’t any longer hide behind “Are you a human?" captcha.\nAs agen
 tic assistants call APIs and act on behalf of users\, core CIAM assumption
 s break: who is the actor\, how is consent captured\, and how is least pri
 vilege enforced across tokens and services. And what if the user decides t
 o disclaim responsibility of a transaction their agent has just completed?
  Modern CIAM needs to evolve to address these issues.\nThis session shows 
 how to adapt CIAM for agent-driven access using delegated authorization\, 
 fine-grained consent\, and continuous verification\, without breaking user
  experience.\nLearn practical patterns to secure consumer journeys when AI
  becomes the user.\nSession Presented by:\n\nDetails: https://identiverse.
 com/idv26/session/?idvid=4076644\n\nSpeakers: Sonal Srivastava (VP – Sol
 utions Advisory • CyberSolve) | Eugert Jani (Senior Director of Access M
 anagement • CyberSolve)\n\nSession Type: SESSION\n\nAll times are in Pac
 ific Daylight Time (PDT / UTC-7)
LOCATION:Breakers J
