BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:identiverse-2026-event-4184120@identiverse.com
SEQUENCE:0
DTSTAMP:20260612T220134Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260616T151000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260616T153500
SUMMARY:Eliminating Standing Privilege: How to Make ZSP Work in the Real Wo
 rld (PDT)
DESCRIPTION:Standing privilege remains one of the most persistent gaps in m
 odern identity security. Once attackers gain valid credentials\, persisten
 t privileged access allows them to move laterally\, escalate privileges\, 
 and operate undetected. While the concept of Zero Standing Privilege (ZSP)
  is widely accepted\, many organizations struggle to translate the princip
 le into practice at enterprise scale.\nIn this session\, Frank Vukovits\, 
 Chief Security Scientist at Delinea\, and John Martinez\, Technical Evange
 list at StrongDM\, will explore how organizations can operationalize ZSP u
 sing real-time\, just-in-time access across infrastructure\, cloud\, and S
 aaS environments. The discussion will focus on the practical challenges of
  replacing persistent privileged access while maintaining developer produc
 tivity and operational continuity.\nThe session will also examine how the 
 rapid growth of non-human identities\, including service accounts\, automa
 tion\, and emerging AI agents\, is expanding the privileged access and exp
 osure problem and increasing the risks associated with standing privilege.
 \nAttendees will leave with practical strategies for extending existing PA
 M investments while moving toward a scalable model for zero standing privi
 lege across both human and non-human identities.\nSession Presented by:\n\
 nDetails: https://identiverse.com/idv26/session/?idvid=4184120\n\nSpeakers
 : Frank Vukovits (Chief Security Scientist • Delinea)\n\nSession Type: S
 ESSION\n\nAll times are in Pacific Daylight Time (PDT / UTC-7)
LOCATION:Breakers L
