BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:identiverse-2026-event-4184119@identiverse.com
SEQUENCE:0
DTSTAMP:20260612T220134Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260616T155000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260616T162000
SUMMARY:The Identity Problem Nobody's Talking About: AI Agents That Deceive
  (PDT)
DESCRIPTION:We've spent years solving the problem of verifying who is acces
 sing a system. But what happens when the entity requesting access can fabr
 icate its own context\, misrepresent its purpose\, and construct a convinc
 ing identity that no MFA prompt will ever catch?\nAI agents don't just aut
 henticate. They reason\, communicate\, and act. This creates an entirely n
 ew class of identity risk that the industry has barely begun to address: a
 gents that deceive. Whether through adversarial manipulation or other mean
 s\, AI agents can present false claims about their identity\, their delega
 ted authority\, and their intended actions–all while passing every tradi
 tional security check.\nIn this session\, we'll unpack the emerging threat
  landscape around AI agent intent\, explore why existing controls fall sho
 rt. The identity perimeter has moved. This session will show you where it'
 s going\, and what to build next.\nSession Presented by:\n\nDetails: https
 ://identiverse.com/idv26/session/?idvid=4184119\n\nSpeakers: Vamseedhar Re
 ddy M (Director of Product\, Trust & Safety • Tinder) | Shimon Modi (Sr.
  Vice President of Product • Arkose Labs)\n\nSession Type: SESSION\n\nAl
 l times are in Pacific Daylight Time (PDT / UTC-7)
LOCATION:Breakers L
