BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:identiverse-2026-event-3931675@identiverse.com
SEQUENCE:0
DTSTAMP:20260612T220134Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260616T155500
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260616T162000
SUMMARY:Operating in the Gaps: Why the “Edge Case” is My Mission-Critic
 al Use Case (PDT)
DESCRIPTION:Products and Standards often solve for the Pareto Principle whe
 re Single Sign-On with MFA via a dedicated piece of hardware for scanning 
 RFID tags or performing an experiment on a linear accelerator beam line is
  an edge case. In a laboratory environment\, it’s the mission-critical 8
 0%.\nDuring a deployment over the last 18 months of phishing resistant MFA
 \, we have found many points of friction in the usual dichotomy of “Work
 force” vs. “Consumer”\, or “Enterprise” vs. Non-Enterprise”. D
 rawing from a large scale rollout at a highly complex research environment
 \, I will examine how “good enough for consumers” contrasted with “r
 igid enough for workforce” often creates the very gaps our mission criti
 cal use cases inhabit.\n\nDetails: https://identiverse.com/idv26/session/?
 idvid=3931675\n\nSpeakers: Shannon Roddy (Systems Engineer • Lawrence Be
 rkeley National Laboratory)\n\nSession Type: SESSION\n\nAll times are in P
 acific Daylight Time (PDT / UTC-7)
LOCATION:Mandalay Bay I
CLASS:PUBLIC
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:OPAQUE
X-MICROSOFT-CDO-INTENDEDSTATUS:BUSY
