UID:identiverse-2026-event-4122713@identiverse.com
SEQUENCE:0
DTSTAMP:20260612T220134Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260616T155500
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260616T162000
SUMMARY:The Governance Fabric (PDT)
DESCRIPTION:Traditional access reviews in Identity Governance and Administr
 ation (IGA) programs often rely on static entitlement data\, leading to in
 effective “rubber-stamping” and limited risk visibility. This session 
 introduces a Context-Aware Access Review Framework—an IGA-agnostic appro
 ach that transforms access certifications into intelligence-driven\, risk-
 informed decisions. The framework augments existing IGA platforms by integ
 rating behavioral telemetry from SIEM systems\, peer group analytics\, and
  data sensitivity insights from governance platforms such as Collibra and 
 Databricks. It generates a comprehensive “identity footprint” for each
  account\, including access usage patterns\, anomalies\, privilege levels\
 , and exposure to sensitive data. By presenting reviewers with contextual 
 insights\, risk scores\, and peer comparisons\, the framework enables more
  informed and defensible decisions—shifting access reviews from periodic
  compliance exercises to continuous governance mechanisms. The approach no
 t only strengthens security posture and enforces least privilege but also 
 enhances auditability and operational efficiency. Attendees will gain a pr
 actical blueprint for implementing an intelligence layer on top of existin
 g IGA investments\, without disrupting current systems\, and learn how to 
 evolve access reviews into a meaningful\, risk-driven governance capabilit
 y.\nSession Presented by:\n\nDetails: https://identiverse.com/idv26/sessio
 n/?idvid=4122713\n\nSpeakers: Aman Rustagi (Partner • ASB Infotech)\n\nS
 ession Type: SESSION\n\nAll times are in Pacific Daylight Time (PDT / UTC-
 7)
LOCATION:Breakers J
