BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:identiverse-2026-event-4122715@identiverse.com
SEQUENCE:0
DTSTAMP:20260612T220134Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260616T163000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260616T165500
SUMMARY:Why You’ll Start Building Agents for Identity Security - But End 
 Up Buying… (PDT)
DESCRIPTION:Most teams that explore building AI agents for Identity securit
 y start with confidence. The use cases seem scoped\, the data is accessibl
 e\, and the logic looks straightforward - until the edge cases multiply\, 
 the maintenance burden grows\, and the security requirements compound. The
  build is live. The problem isn't solved. Great Identity leaders learn thi
 s lesson early. They measure success by what got done: access cleaned up\,
  policies enforced\, and risk remediated. And increasingly\, they're choos
 ing to buy purpose-built agents rather than maintain homegrown ones that c
 onsume engineering cycles without delivering security outcomes.In this ses
 sion\, Nadav Erez breaks down the build-vs-buy decision that every Identit
 y team faces. and why the calculus almost always shifts toward buying once
  you factor in factors such as security depth\, domain expertise\, and the
  true cost of keeping agents operational over time.Join us to learn how to
  make the right call for your organization - and why the teams moving fast
 est on Agentic IAM are those who stopped building and started deploying.\n
 Session Presented by:\n\nDetails: https://identiverse.com/idv26/session/?i
 dvid=4122715\n\nSpeakers: Nadav Erez (CTO / Co-Founder • Twine Security)
 \n\nSession Type: SESSION\n\nAll times are in Pacific Daylight Time (PDT /
  UTC-7)
LOCATION:Breakers L
CLASS:PUBLIC
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:OPAQUE
