BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:identiverse-2026-event-4184116@identiverse.com
SEQUENCE:0
DTSTAMP:20260612T220134Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260616T163000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260616T165500
SUMMARY:Agentic AI Identity Governance — Governing the inheritance chain:
  human\, agent\, and machine identity (PDT)
DESCRIPTION:Digital identity has always been chaotic. However\, just as IAM
  and cybersecurity teams began gaining traction in managing human and non-
 human identities\, the rapid rise of AI has increased the chaos – making
  prior identity efforts incomplete.\nAI agents are already spreading acros
 s the enterprise\, often without approval\, visibility\, or control. This 
 is the reality of shadow AI\, and it’s introducing a fast-growing set of
  security risks and compliance gaps. Ignoring it won’t slow it down — 
 it will only make the problem harder to contain.\nTo respond\, organizatio
 ns need to fundamentally rethink governance. AI agents must be treated as 
 digital workers\, with defined identities\, trust relationships\, and priv
 ileges\, not as tools operating outside existing controls.\nIn this sessio
 n\, CISOs and IAM leaders will learn:\nWhy their organizations need to mov
 e quickly to address agentic AI identities\nHow unsanctioned AI is acceler
 ating identity sprawl and expanding the attack surface\nWhy AI governance 
 requires creating a unified control plane that can manage human\, non-huma
 n\, and AI identities together.\nSession Presented by:\n\nDetails: https:/
 /identiverse.com/idv26/session/?idvid=4184116\n\nSpeakers: Akshay Srinivas
  Rajanbabu (Distinguished Engineer\, Solution Consulting • Radiant Logic
 ) | Jason Joe (IAM Principal Architect • Radiant Logic)\n\nSession Type:
  SESSION\n\nAll times are in Pacific Daylight Time (PDT / UTC-7)
LOCATION:Mandalay Bay D
