BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:identiverse-2026-event-3931756@identiverse.com
SEQUENCE:0
DTSTAMP:20260612T220134Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260616T170500
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260616T173000
SUMMARY:When Identity Becomes the Experience: Higher Education’s Shift fr
 om Accounts to Relationships (PDT)
DESCRIPTION:For decades\, higher education served as a proving ground for d
 igital identity\, pioneering federated trust models\, community‑led stan
 dards\, and large‑scale collaboration long before identity became a comm
 ercial platform market. Today\, that landscape is shifting. Identity archi
 tectures are increasingly shaped by vendor ecosystems\, customer‑centric
  design patterns\, and evolving expectations for frictionless\, privacy‑
 preserving experiences.\nAt the same time\, higher education itself is cha
 nging. Institutions now compete for applicants\, support lifelong learners
 \, issue stackable credentials\, and maintain long‑lived relationships t
 hat extend well beyond traditional degree programs. In this environment\, 
 identity is no longer just account management\, it is the experience and a
  visible signal of trust. Poorly designed identity journeys can silently u
 ndermine engagement\, while adaptive\, relationship‑centric identity can
  become a strategic differentiator.\nThis session examines higher educatio
 n identity through the lens of customer and public identity\, exploring ho
 w CIAM principles\, modern identity fabrics\, and emerging AI‑assisted c
 apabilities can help reconcile long‑lived\, multi‑role relationships w
 ith evolving expectations for security\, usability\, and governance. By sh
 ifting from account‑centric thinking to relationship‑centric design\, 
 higher education offers valuable lessons for any organization building fut
 ure‑ready digital trust at scale.\n\nDetails: https://identiverse.com/id
 v26/session/?idvid=3931756\n\nSpeakers: Robert Mackin (Associate Director 
 of Access Management • The Ohio State University)\n\nSession Type: SESSI
 ON\n\nAll times are in Pacific Daylight Time (PDT / UTC-7)
LOCATION:Mandalay Bay K
