UID:identiverse-2026-event-4067368@identiverse.com
SEQUENCE:0
DTSTAMP:20260612T220134Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260616T170500
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260616T173000
SUMMARY:Identity Security in an Agentic World: Strengthening Posture\, Unlo
 cking Value (PDT)
DESCRIPTION:Identity security is entering a new phase\, one where tradition
 al concepts like users\, roles\, and access requests no longer hold.\nAs A
 I agents\, automation\, and machine identities rapidly proliferate\, enter
 prises are shifting from a world of human-driven access to one defined by 
 autonomous actors operating at scale. To support that transformation\, ide
 ntity solutions must adapt and face the challenge. In this new reality\, a
 ccess is no longer static\, identities are no longer stable\, and governan
 ce can no longer rely on periodic reviews or predefined roles.Monday.com i
 s at the forefront of this agentic transformation\, redefining its interna
 l processes as well as how teams around the world work.\nIn this session\,
  we explore how identity is evolving beyond its current foundations and wh
 at that means for security\, operations\, and risk. We will share real-wor
 ld insights into how Monday.com leverages Linx Security to secure and gove
 rn human\, non-human\, and agentic access at scale.\nThis talk offers a fo
 rward-looking perspective grounded in real-world experience\, providing id
 entity leaders with a framework for navigating the next era of identity se
 curity.\nSession Presented by:\n\nDetails: https://identiverse.com/idv26/s
 ession/?idvid=4067368\n\nSpeakers: Dor Renert (VP of Product • Linx Secu
 rity) | Niv Goldenberg (CPO • Linx Security) | Lior Zagury (Senior Direc
 tor of Global IT & Workforce Tech • monday.com)\n\nSession Type: SESSION
 \n\nAll times are in Pacific Daylight Time (PDT / UTC-7)
LOCATION:Breakers J
