SUMMARY:Beyond Passwords: Building a Modern Identity Security Strategy for 
 the Passkey and AI Era (PDT)
DESCRIPTION:The shift to passwordless is no longer theoretical. Passkeys ar
 e moving into mainstream enterprise deployment\, while AI adoption is crea
 ting a new class of identity risk that many organizations are not yet equi
 pped to govern. Across the market\, 2026 is being framed as a tipping poin
 t: phishing-resistant authentication is becoming table stakes\, and machin
 e and AI identities are expanding faster than traditional controls can han
 dle.\nThis session will explore what a modern identity security strategy n
 ow requires: stronger authentication\, better lifecycle control\, continuo
 us risk evaluation\, and a unified approach across workforce\, customer\, 
 and non-human identities. Rather than layering more tools onto an already 
 fragmented stack\, organizations need a trust-first architecture that alig
 ns security with usability and scale.\nSession Presented by:\n\nDetails: h
 ttps://identiverse.com/idv26/session/?idvid=4070656\n\nSpeakers: Rima Pawa
 r (Sr Director\, Product Management • Entrust)\n\nSession Type: SESSION\
 n\nAll times are in Pacific Daylight Time (PDT / UTC-7)
