DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260616T173000
SUMMARY:2026: When Identity Becomes Workflow (PDT)
DESCRIPTION:How identity context is becoming the execution layer for securi
 ty\, risk\, and compliance.\nAs enterprises adopt more automation\, AI age
 nts\, service accounts\, third parties\, machine identities\, cloud resour
 ces\, and connected systems\, identity context increasingly determines wha
 t work should happen next.\nEvery access exception\, policy violation\, co
 mpliance gap\, onboarding request\, offboarding request\, incident\, or re
 mediation path depends on the same chain of context: what identity is invo
 lved\, what system or resource is affected\, what policy applies\, who app
 roves the action\, what should be automated\, and what evidence needs to e
 xist afterward.\nThis session will explore the next frontier for identity:
  moving from visibility and governance into secure workflow execution.\nTh
 e focus will be on practical patterns for identity-aware automation\, incl
 uding human intervention points\, machine-speed actions\, auditability\, a
 nd turning identity context into governed outcomes across security\, risk\
 , and compliance.\nSession Presented by:\n\nDetails: https://identiverse.c
 om/idv26/session/?idvid=4240994\n\nSpeakers: Nic Chavez (Advisor • Serva
 l)\n\nSession Type: SESSION\n\nAll times are in Pacific Daylight Time (PDT
  / UTC-7)
