BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:identiverse-2026-event-4144358@identiverse.com
SEQUENCE:0
DTSTAMP:20260612T220134Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260616T174000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260616T175500
SUMMARY:Tech Theater Presented by WSO2 LLC: Contextual Identity: One Model 
 for Humans\, Systems\, and Agents (PDT)
DESCRIPTION:Traditional IAM recognizes two principal types: humans who log 
 in with intent\, and systems that hold credentials and make predictable ca
 lls. Every authorization\, audit\, and consent model is built around that 
 split.Agents fit neither. They run autonomously\, invoke tools in unplanne
 d combinations\, and delegate to other agents\, putting several execution 
 steps between the original human intent and the final action. IAM built fo
 r direct user-to-systems or system-to-system calls has no model for what h
 appens in between.This session proposes contextual identity: a single abst
 raction where every principal\, whether human\, system\, or agent\, is rep
 resented as who they are\, who delegated to them\, and what they are curre
 ntly doing. Authorization evaluates the full chain\, not just the caller a
 t the door.No new principal type. No protocol patches. One abstraction tha
 t works across all three.\n\nDetails: https://identiverse.com/idv26/sessio
 n/?idvid=4144358\n\nSession Type: TECH THEATER\n\nAll times are in Pacific
  Daylight Time (PDT / UTC-7)
LOCATION:Tech Theater 1
CLASS:PUBLIC
STATUS:CONFIRMED
