SUMMARY:NHAI Pavilion Panel: Is MCP Dead\, Alive or About to Matter (PDT)
DESCRIPTION:The Model Context Protocol promised a standard way for agents t
 o connect to tools and services. But CLI-native approaches and direct API 
 integrations are challenging whether a protocol layer is even necessary. T
 his session examines where MCP is gaining real traction\, where it is bein
 g bypassed\, and what the MCP versus CLI debate reveals about standardisat
 ion in agentic architectures. Attendees will leave with a grounded view of
  whether MCP deserves investment\, monitoring\, or reconsideration in thei
 r own stack.\n\nDetails: https://identiverse.com/idv26/session/?idvid=4216
 662\n\nSession Type: NON-HUMAN & AI IDENTITY PAVILION\n\nAll times are in 
 Pacific Daylight Time (PDT / UTC-7)
