SUMMARY:Power Breakfast Presented by Orchid Security: From Seeing to Knowin
 g: The Identity Observability Frontier (PDT)
DESCRIPTION:Visibility was the first battle. We built dashboards\, access r
 eviews\, and certification workflows. We learned to see our identity lands
 cape. But seeing isn't knowing. Knowing means understanding what identitie
 s are actually doing inside your applications — not what policies say sh
 ould happen\, but what executes. In the agentic era\, that distinction is 
 no longer academic. Agents act at machine speed\, on stale permissions\, w
 ith no owner and no trace. Visibility can't catch that. Observability can.
  This session explores the frontier between seeing and knowing and why clo
 sing it is identity security's next imperative.\n\nDetails: https://identi
 verse.com/idv26/session/?idvid=4086811\n\nSession Type: POWER BREAKFAST\n\
 nAll times are in Pacific Daylight Time (PDT / UTC-7)
LOCATION:Oceanside F
