DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260617T071500
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260617T081500
SUMMARY:Power Breakfast Presented by Rubrik: After-Action Report: What a To
 rnado's Failed Emergency Response Teaches Identity Security About AI-Era R
 esilience (PDT)
DESCRIPTION:On May 16\, 2025\, an EF3 tornado struck St. Louis. The warning
  sirens never sounded. The independent after-action report found cascading
  failures: untested alert systems\, a single-point-of-failure repeater\, u
 nclear ownership between agencies\, a 22-year-old emergency plan\, and sil
 oed teams who couldn't coordinate under pressure. Every failure maps direc
 tly to what we see in identity incident response today. Drawing from the o
 fficial investigation\, IR Readiness Scorecard data showing 99% of organiz
 ations score "Not Ready\," and the compressed attack timelines of AI-accel
 erated threats\, this session explores what disaster response teaches us a
 bout rebuilding identity infrastructure.\n\nDetails: https://identiverse.c
 om/idv26/session/?idvid=4134856\n\nSession Type: POWER BREAKFAST\n\nAll ti
 mes are in Pacific Daylight Time (PDT / UTC-7)
LOCATION:Oceanside G
