UID:identiverse-2026-event-4005895@identiverse.com
SEQUENCE:0
DTSTAMP:20260612T220134Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260617T090000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260617T093000
SUMMARY:Why the Identity Industry Needs More Bicyclists (PDT)
DESCRIPTION:Working in cybersecurity sometimes feels like being trapped in 
 the movie “Groundhog Day\,” with the same vulnerabilities being exploi
 ted by the same bad actors year after year after year. We know that passwo
 rds aren’t worth the paper they’re written on (and let’s face it\, y
 ou still have colleagues writing down passwords)\, legacy MFA can be phish
 ed\, and knowledge-based verification is easily compromised – and yet\, 
 we still cling to these tools rather than replace them. Do you know who do
 esn’t put up with awful security? Bicyclists! In this keynote\, Jeremy w
 ill talk about how bicyclists dealt with one of the security world’s mos
 t jarring vulnerabilities and addressed it quickly and decisively – and 
 discuss how the biking community can teach our community a thing or two.\n
 \nDetails: https://identiverse.com/idv26/session/?idvid=4005895\n\nSpeaker
 s: Jeremy Grant (Coordinator • Better Identity Coalition)\n\nSession Typ
 e: KEYNOTE\n\nAll times are in Pacific Daylight Time (PDT / UTC-7)
LOCATION:Oceanside
