UID:identiverse-2026-event-4216664@identiverse.com
SEQUENCE:0
DTSTAMP:20260612T220134Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260617T101500
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260617T104500
SUMMARY:NHAI Pavilion Panel: When Agents Create Agents: Identity Explosion 
 and Containment (PDT)
DESCRIPTION:Agentic systems don’t scale linearly\, they spawn. This sessi
 on looks at what happens when agents dynamically create other agents\, eac
 h requiring identity\, permissions\, and lifecycle management. We’ll dis
 cuss identity sprawl\, blast radius\, revocation challenges\, and the limi
 ts of today’s provisioning models. Attendees will gain practical insight
  into how to think about containment\, hierarchy\, and trust boundaries in
  agent-driven systems.\n\nDetails: https://identiverse.com/idv26/session/?
 idvid=4216664\n\nSession Type: NON-HUMAN & AI IDENTITY PAVILION\n\nAll tim
 es are in Pacific Daylight Time (PDT / UTC-7)
