DTSTAMP:20260612T220134Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260617T104500
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260617T110000
SUMMARY:NHAI Pavilion Presented by Lumos: Not All NHIs Are Created Equal: W
 hy Service Accounts\, API Keys and AI Agents Need Different Controls (PDT)
DESCRIPTION:Humans wait days for access and keep it forever. Machines scatt
 er across systems with no clear owner. Agents execute\, chain decisions\, 
 and generate access paths no one explicitly approved. Three identity types
 \, three broken models\, and most IAM programs were only built for one of 
 them.\nIn this session\, Andrej Safundzic breaks down exactly how each ide
 ntity type exposes a different failure in today's IAM model and what it ta
 kes to govern all three at once. You'll learn:\nWhy provisioning and gover
 nance are the wrong control points for the modern identity landscape\nWher
 e risk hides across each identity type: dynamic access\, missing ownership
 \, and self-directed workflows\nWhy visibility without enforcement is just
  lagging insight\nHow to move to a runtime control model that acts in real
  time\nAI isn’t just another identity problem. It requires a new control
  plane and a shift in how teams approach it.\n\nDetails: https://identiver
 se.com/idv26/session/?idvid=4187968\n\nSession Type: NON-HUMAN & AI IDENTI
 TY PAVILION\n\nAll times are in Pacific Daylight Time (PDT / UTC-7)
LOCATION:NHAI Pavilion Theater
