UID:identiverse-2026-event-3931667@identiverse.com
SEQUENCE:0
DTSTAMP:20260612T220134Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260617T113000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260617T122000
SUMMARY:Engineering Trust at Scale: Combating Identity Fraud with Adaptive\
 , Intelligence-driven Identity Capabilities (PDT)
DESCRIPTION:Identity fraud has become an industrialized\, AI-powered threat
 —scaling faster than many of the identity systems designed to stop it. F
 rom synthetic identities and deepfakes to automated account takeovers\, to
 day’s attacks exploit static controls and fragmented identity architectu
 res across every industry.\nThis session will reframe identity fraud as a 
 business challenge\, not just a compliance problem. We will explore how or
 ganizations can engineer trust at scale using intelligence-driven identity
  capabilities—combining advanced verification\, behavioral signals\, ris
 k-adaptive authentication\, and emerging decentralized identity models. At
 tendees will learn how modern identity architectures can help reduce fraud
  without adding friction\, adapt in real time to evolving threats\, and su
 pport growth across complex digital ecosystems.\nDesigned for identity and
  security leaders\, this talk will deliver practical\, cross-industry insi
 ghts on building resilient\, future-ready identity systems in an era where
  trust is constantly under attack.\n\nDetails: https://identiverse.com/idv
 26/session/?idvid=3931667\n\nSpeakers: Alex Bolante (Partner/Managing Dire
 ctor • Deloitte & Touche LLP)\n\nSession Type: MASTERCLASS\n\nAll times 
 are in Pacific Daylight Time (PDT / UTC-7)
LOCATION:Mandalay Bay K
