UID:identiverse-2026-event-3931718@identiverse.com
SEQUENCE:0
DTSTAMP:20260612T220134Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260617T113000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260617T122000
SUMMARY:Beyond RBAC: Why Your Access Model Cannot Stop AI Data Leaks (PDT)
DESCRIPTION:Your RBAC system says yes. Your AI reveals classified intellige
 nce. A hospital administrator queries within her role\, and AI returns ful
 l PHI. An analyst accesses unclassified data\, and AI compiles it into Top
  Secret. Same failure\, different regulations violated. Traditional IAM au
 thenticates users and grants database access\, but generative AI synthesiz
 es data in ways that shatter HIPAA minimum necessary rules and trigger cla
 ssification by compilation. This isn't theoretical: federal agencies and h
 ealthcare organizations are discovering these gaps in production right now
 . Learn how the identical access control vulnerability creates classificat
 ion violations in government and HIPAA violations in healthcare\, and walk
  away with a layered framework that stops AI data leaks before they leave 
 the system. Real implementations\, live demonstrations\, practical roadmap
 . Vendor neutral and immediately applicable.\n\nDetails: https://identiver
 se.com/idv26/session/?idvid=3931718\n\nSpeakers: Christopher Hunt (Senior 
 Identity Engineer • Uberether)\n\nSession Type: MASTERCLASS\n\nAll times
  are in Pacific Daylight Time (PDT / UTC-7)
LOCATION:Mandalay Bay H
CLASS:PUBLIC
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:OPAQUE
X-MICROSOFT-CDO-INTENDEDSTATUS:BUSY
