SUMMARY:Hands-On Agentic Authorization: Building Identity-Aware Tool Contro
 l with Cisco (PDT)
DESCRIPTION:AI agents running on the Model Context Protocol (MCP) are the f
 astest-growing class of non-human identity in the enterprise — and tradi
 tional IAM wasn't built for them.\nIn this Masterclass\, we walk through a
  complete agentic authorization system: onboarding an MCP server\, configu
 ring fine-grained tool-level policies\, authenticating an AI agent via OAu
 th 2.1/OIDC through Duo SSO\, and watching access decisions execute in rea
 l time based on human user identity.\nTo be discussed— OAuth 2.1 token f
 lows\, why HTTP 403 breaks MCP clients\, the three disconnected authorizat
 ion layers (network\, tool\, OAuth scope) and how to unify them.\nSession 
 Presented by:\n\nDetails: https://identiverse.com/idv26/session/?idvid=405
 6439\n\nSpeakers: Dros Adamson (Principal Software Engineer • Cisco Duo)
  | Colin Medfisch (Senior Product Manager • Cisco Duo)\n\nSession Type: 
