SUMMARY:Modern Authentication in AI World (PDT)
DESCRIPTION:This masterclass provides developers with a comprehensive techn
 ical overview of modern sign-in\, account recovery\, and platform safety s
 olutions. Recognizing that static authentication policies are increasingly
  insufficient against sophisticated threats\, this session explores three 
 critical tools designed to dynamically secure user journeys and reduce dev
 elopment friction.\nThrough practical use cases and live technical demos\,
  the presentation will cover:\nSign in with Google Security Bundle: Implem
 enting focused and robust authentication to elevate user security. We will
  cover developer best practices for utilizing the latest OpenID Connect (O
 IDC) session metadata claims to enforce dynamic access controls\, trigger 
 step-up authentication\, and prevent account takeovers.Gemini Connect: Eli
 minating fragmented identities and high LLM API costs by allowing users to
  bring their own Gemini subscriptions to your application via Sign in with
  Google\, accelerating the path to production.We will share actionable str
 ategies and proven frameworks to build secure\, cost-effective\, and intel
 ligent authentication flows.\nSession Presented by:\n\nDetails: https://id
 entiverse.com/idv26/session/?idvid=4056444\n\nSpeakers: Molly Zhang (Softw
 are Engineer • Google) | Sergei Akulich (Product Manager • Google)\n\n
 Session Type: MASTERCLASS\n\nAll times are in Pacific Daylight Time (PDT /
  UTC-7)
