SUMMARY:Tech Theater Presented by Bridgesoft: Wheels Up: How an Airline Cus
 tomer in the Aviation Industry Re-Platformed Identity Governance (PDT)
DESCRIPTION:Every identity team eventually faces the same question: keep pa
 tching the platform we have\, or make a move? For our esteemed airline cli
 ent - a national low-cost carrier running 24/7 operations across pilots\, 
 ground crews\, maintenance\, corporate\, and contract staff - the answer r
 eshaped how the airline governs access.\nIn this fifteen-minute fireside\,
  a senior identity leader from our client tells the story of replacing the
  airline's legacy identity governance solution with Bridgesoft. It's a can
 did\, peer-to-peer conversation: what was shifting in the environment that
  forced a rethink\, how the team evaluated the market\, what the implement
 ation actually felt like\, and what's measurably different today - in audi
 t cycles\, onboarding speed\, and the hours the team got back.\nThis isn't
  a product pitch. It's a practitioner's account of a high-stakes transitio
 n at the scale and tempo of commercial aviation\, with the specific\, tran
 sferable lessons that only come from having done it. If you're staring at 
 your own aging IGA and wondering whether and how to move\, this is the con
 versation to sit in on.\n\nDetails: https://identiverse.com/idv26/session/
 ?idvid=4211982\n\nSession Type: TECH THEATER\n\nAll times are in Pacific D
 aylight Time (PDT / UTC-7)
LOCATION:Tech Theater 2
