DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260617T142500
SUMMARY:The Odyssey – A Journey through the Verifiable Digital Credential
  Ecosystem (PDT)
DESCRIPTION:Verifiable Digital Credentials are at a critical inflection poi
 nt. The technology is maturing\, the standards are progressing\, and inter
 national organizations are increasingly looking to the technology as a mea
 ns to provide more effective and secure access to critical services. Yet\,
  scaled adoption - particularly in online scenarios - remains just out of 
 reach. In 2023\, NIST launched a project in their National Cybersecurity C
 enter of Excellence (NCCoE) to not only assist in the advancement of the t
 echnology and standards supporting Verifiable Digital Credentials but also
  explore the opportunities and challenges related to relying party adoptio
 n. This project has reached the conclusion of its initial phase\, which fo
 cused on enabling financial institutions to adopt Mobile Drivers Licences 
 (a specific typeof Verifiable Digital Credentials) for identity verificati
 on. In this presentation\, the poject leads Bill Fisher and Ryan Galluzzo 
 will bring attendees along on the Verifiable Digital Credential journey th
 at has unfolded over the course of the project. From inception to conclusi
 on\, the presentation will explore key lessons\, challenges\, and opportun
 ities identified with a team of over 20 project collaborators including: m
 ajor United States banks\, critical technology providers\, states\, federa
 l agenceis\, and organizations creating the technical framework and standa
 rds that wills serve as the foundation of the Verifiable Digital Credentia
 l ecosystem.\n\nDetails: https://identiverse.com/idv26/session/?idvid=3931
 741\n\nSpeakers: Ryan Galluzzo (Identity Program Lead • National Institu
 te of Standards and Technology) | William Fisher (Security Engineer • NI
 ST)\n\nSession Type: SESSION\n\nAll times are in Pacific Daylight Time (PD
 T / UTC-7)
LOCATION:Mandalay Bay F
CLASS:PUBLIC
