SUMMARY:The Passkey Reality Check: Addressing 2025’s Biggest Misconceptio
 ns (PDT)
DESCRIPTION:Another session on passkeys? Well we're entering year four\, an
 d passkeys are available to billions of users. However\, widespread availa
 bility hasn't necessarily led to widespread understanding. From concerns a
 bout workforce suitability to fears of biometric theft and vendor lock-in\
 , the same old myths are evolving into new misunderstandings. This session
  revisits the passkey landscape to address the questions that remain after
  another year of massive growth. We’ll tackle myths regarding sync fabri
 cs\, workforce usage\, credential manager portability\, and more. This ses
 sion will provide a reality check on what passkeys actually do\, what they
  don't\, which capabilities are available for different use cases\, and ho
 w to separate marketing hype and sensationalist headlines from facts.\n\nD
 etails: https://identiverse.com/idv26/session/?idvid=3931712\n\nSpeakers: 
 Tim Cappalli (Sr. Architect\, Identity Standards • Okta) | Matthew Mille
 r (Senior Technical Lead • Cisco Duo) | Nishant Kaushik (CTO • FIDO Al
 liance)\n\nSession Type: SESSION\n\nAll times are in Pacific Daylight Time
  (PDT / UTC-7)
LOCATION:Mandalay Bay I
