UID:identiverse-2026-event-3931742@identiverse.com
SEQUENCE:0
DTSTAMP:20260612T220134Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260617T143500
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260617T150000
SUMMARY:Trust Me (PDT)
DESCRIPTION:Everything we do as a society relies on trust: trust that syste
 ms will do what we expect\, trust that the parties we act with are genuine
 \, trust that the results that we get are valid. Trust is essential and co
 ntextual\, born of assumptions and rooted in norms but also the foundation
  for those assumptions and norms.\nThe same is true online. The internet's
  security layers provide mechanisms for trust in what we do every day\, bu
 t these protocols and systems were built with a specific world in mind. Wh
 en these assumptions are challenged\, can we still trust the system built 
 upon them?\nIn this talk\, we'll take a look at how trust can be challenge
 d by things like AI agents\, easily generated data\, and human-mimicking c
 omputer systems. We'll talk about how these new ways of looking at the wor
 ld are changing how we build things. Maybe we'll even find a good way forw
 ard in all of this\, one that we can all trust.\n\nDetails: https://identi
 verse.com/idv26/session/?idvid=3931742\n\nSpeakers: Justin Richer (Senior 
 Staff Engineer • MongoDB)\n\nSession Type: SESSION\n\nAll times are in P
 acific Daylight Time (PDT / UTC-7)
LOCATION:Mandalay Bay K
