SUMMARY:From Teens to Terriers & Try Lines: How Australian banks are confir
 ming customer identity via the ConnectID Network (PDT)
DESCRIPTION:From teenagers signing up for their first social media app or d
 og breeders registering a litter\, through to a rugby club managing member
 ships\, everyday identity checks just got a whole lot easier for Australia
 ns aged 16 and above. Run by industry body Australian Payments Plus\, the 
 ConnectID network supports participating banks to vouch for their existing
 \, eligible customers to accredited Relying Parties. Hear from Linden Daws
 on at the National Australia Bank on their ConnectID journey so far\, incl
 uding lessons learned from the recent introduction of the Social Media Min
 imum Age federal government legislation designed to keep young Aussies saf
 er online.\n\nDetails: https://identiverse.com/idv26/session/?idvid=393173
 4\n\nSpeakers: Linden Dawson (Customer Digital Identity\, Senior Product M
 anager • National Australia Bank)\n\nSession Type: SESSION\n\nAll times 
 are in Pacific Daylight Time (PDT / UTC-7)
LOCATION:Mandalay Bay F
