BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:identiverse-2026-event-3931762@identiverse.com
SEQUENCE:0
DTSTAMP:20260612T220134Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260617T143500
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260617T150000
SUMMARY:Deepfakes\, Synthetic IDs\, and “Invisible” Takeovers: A Layere
 d Identity Defense for Onboarding\, Account Recovery\, and Payments (PDT)
DESCRIPTION:Identity-based fraud is evolving from “stolen credentials” 
 to AI-amplified deception: synthetic identities\, deepfake-driven verifica
 tion bypass\, and polished social engineering that targets onboarding and 
 account recovery first. Gartner notes that GenAI enables fake identities a
 nd deepfakes\, including both presentation attacks (shown to cameras) and 
 injection attacks (digitally inserted)\, pushing IAM teams to demand layer
 ed defenses beyond “basic liveness.”\nIn this session\, we’ll map a 
 practical\, cross-sector defense model that connects identity proofing\, a
 uthentication\, and fraud/risk signals across the customer lifecycle—fro
 m KYC/KYB onboarding through step-up authentication and high-risk transact
 ions. We’ll show how to pressure-test vendors and internal controls (met
 adata inspection\, payload integrity checks\, contextual risk) and how to 
 modernize the weak link most orgs overlook: credential enrollment and acco
 unt recovery.\nAttendees leave with a usable blueprint and evaluation chec
 klist they can apply immediately\, without turning the talk into a product
  pitch.\n\nDetails: https://identiverse.com/idv26/session/?idvid=3931762\n
 \nSpeakers: Conor White (President- Strategic Initiatives • Daon)\n\nSes
 sion Type: SESSION\n\nAll times are in Pacific Daylight Time (PDT / UTC-7)
LOCATION:Mandalay Bay H
CLASS:PUBLIC
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:OPAQUE
