SUMMARY:Reimagining IAM: Identity Data as the Engine of Zero Trust (PDT)
DESCRIPTION:Identity data is rapidly becoming the foundation of modern secu
 rity\, yet its value is often underestimated outside of IAM teams. While i
 dentity practitioners recognize the power of centralized\, high-quality id
 entity data\, executive stakeholders often struggle to connect it to tangi
 ble security outcomes. This session explores how identity data evolves fro
 m a backend integration challenge into a strategic enabler of Zero Trust. 
 By unlocking identity context\, centralized risk scoring\, and real-time r
 esponsiveness to security operations\, organizations can transform IAM int
 o a core driver of cybersecurity effectiveness.\nSession Presented by:\n\n
 Details: https://identiverse.com/idv26/session/?idvid=4184117\n\nSpeakers:
  David Moosavifazel (Director of Identity & Domain Services • AdventHeal
 th) | Andrew Pagels (Senior Manager of Identity Management • AdventHealt
 h)\n\nSession Type: SESSION\n\nAll times are in Pacific Daylight Time (PDT
  / UTC-7)
