SUMMARY:Biometric Injection Attacks (PDT)
DESCRIPTION:As biometric authentication increasingly secures digital identi
 ties\, the need to ensure its resilience against sophisticated threats\, p
 articularly injection attacks\, is paramount. These attacks involve the ma
 nipulation of biometric data at various points within the authentication p
 ipeline to bypass security controls.\nThis presentation will offer a deep 
 dive into the evolving landscape of biometric injection attacks. It will c
 over the latest threat trends\, testing methodologies\, emerging standards
 \, and best practices necessary for accurately assessing a biometric syste
 m's ability to withstand these threats.\nThe rapid emergence of injection 
 attacks as the primary threat in the biometrics industry underscores the u
 rgency of developing a robust assurance and testing framework.\nFurthermor
 e\, injection attack testing is key to establishing and maintaining trust 
 in biometric authentication\, ensuring a user experience that is both secu
 re and resilient throughout the entire account lifecycle.\n\nDetails: http
 s://identiverse.com/idv26/session/?idvid=3931708\n\nSpeakers: Alastair Tre
 harne (Co-Founder • Ingenium Biometric Laboratories) | Chris Allgrove (D
 irector and Co-Founder • Ingenium Biometrics)\n\nSession Type: SESSION\n
 \nAll times are in Pacific Daylight Time (PDT / UTC-7)
LOCATION:Mandalay Bay H
