BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:identiverse-2026-event-3931706@identiverse.com
SEQUENCE:0
DTSTAMP:20260612T220134Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260617T151000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260617T153500
SUMMARY:Signal Overload: Reconciling High-Velocity Identity with API-Based 
 Management (PDT)
DESCRIPTION:"Continuous Identity" is the next frontier of access control\, 
 with standards like SSE and CAEP providing the critical signals that allow
  policy engines to make dynamic access decisions. However\, as we move tow
 ard near-real-time signal evaluation\, we face an emerging architectural c
 ollision course: the friction between a constant flow of small attribute c
 hanges and the limitations of traditional API-based identity lifecycle man
 agement.\nWhile real-time authorization is a compelling vision\, it introd
 uces significant risks when applied to enterprise-scale environments. This
  session examines the looming challenge of maintaining identity persistenc
 e when a constant flow of near-real-time updates outpaces the rate limits\
 , eventual consistency models\, and structural constraints of SaaS identit
 y management APIs. We will analyze the "split-brain" state - where the dyn
 amic authorization layer and the persistent identity store diverge - and w
 hy Just-In-Time (JIT) access patterns are often at odds with durable\, API
 -driven lifecycle management.\nJoin us for a deep dive into these emerging
  technical frictions. This session provides the architectural awareness ne
 cessary to evaluate the trade-offs between signal velocity and data integr
 ity. Attendees will leave with a framework for questioning current system 
 limitations\, ensuring their identity strategy is prepared for the high-vo
 lume\, near-real-time realities of the future.\n\nDetails: https://identiv
 erse.com/idv26/session/?idvid=3931706\n\nSpeakers: Danny Zollner (Senior I
 dentity Standards Architect • Okta)\n\nSession Type: SESSION\n\nAll time
 s are in Pacific Daylight Time (PDT / UTC-7)
LOCATION:Mandalay Bay I
CLASS:PUBLIC
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:OPAQUE
