DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260617T153500
SUMMARY:The End of SSO? Rethinking One Trust Fits All (PDT)
DESCRIPTION:The promise of SSO is betrayed by the possibility of having our
  IDP’s used against us. As the fundamental building block for Zero Trust
 \, SSOs consolidation of visibility\, control\, policy and access has made
  it the most attractive target for attacker – control of this one system
  yields all of them. Are we better off retreating to a world of app identi
 ty? Can we imagine a world where we retain the benefits of SSO while creat
 ing effective crash bulkheads in our digital ecosystems? Alex will examine
  the achilles heel of systemic identity compromise\, and explore how curre
 nt generation techologies can built a more resilient future system without
  giving up on the benefits of SSO.\n\nDetails: https://identiverse.com/idv
 26/session/?idvid=3931719\n\nSpeakers: Alexander Weinert (Chief Product Of
 ficer • Semperis)\n\nSession Type: SESSION\n\nAll times are in Pacific D
 aylight Time (PDT / UTC-7)
LOCATION:Mandalay Bay K
