SUMMARY:Why Active Directory Is Still Your Biggest Identity Risk (PDT)
DESCRIPTION:90% of enterprises still run Active Directory – but it's ofte
 n a garage that desperately needs spring cleaning. AD is a haven for servi
 ce accounts nobody owns\, dormant identities nobody monitors\, and legacy 
 protocols nobody can put MFA in front of. This mess leaves organizations o
 pen to attackers. Cisco Talos found 44% of identity-based attacks target A
 D.\nIn this session\, learn how to effectively extend identity security po
 sture management (ISPM) to on-premises AD - and then protect what you find
  through proactive clean up and inserting MFA directly at the domain contr
 oller. It’s time to clean out the AD garage.\nSession Presented by:\n\nD
 etails: https://identiverse.com/idv26/session/?idvid=4056445\n\nSpeakers: 
 Lars Urbaniak (Director of Product Management • Cisco Duo)\n\nSession Ty
 pe: SESSION\n\nAll times are in Pacific Daylight Time (PDT / UTC-7)
