DTSTAMP:20260612T220134Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260617T155500
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260617T162000
SUMMARY:The Hard Part of Policy Based Access Control Nobody Talks About (PD
 T)
DESCRIPTION:Policy Based Access Control promises fine grained\, context awa
 re authorization\, but many organizations struggle to adopt it at scale. T
 he biggest barrier is not the model itself. It is the difficulty of author
 ing\, validating\, and maintaining policies that accurately reflect real a
 ccess intent.\nMost access intent is expressed in natural language through
  design docs\, tickets\, audits\, and reviews. Recently\, teams have start
 ed exploring AI to convert this intent directly into authorization policie
 s. While this sounds appealing\, early experiments show it is easier said 
 than done. AI generated policies often look correct but contain subtle fla
 ws such as missing conditions\, ambiguous subjects\, or overly permissive 
 defaults. These mistakes can quietly introduce serious access risks.\nThis
  session explores how natural language can still be a powerful entry point
  for PBAC when paired with the right guardrails. It discusses the risks of
  raw AI driven policy generation\, why those risks matter for authorizatio
 n\, and how a structured pipeline using validation\, constraints\, and hum
 an review can help bridge intent and enforcement safely. The focus is on m
 aking PBAC practical without turning policy automation into a new attack s
 urface\n\nDetails: https://identiverse.com/idv26/session/?idvid=3931765\n\
 nSpeakers: Vatsal Gupta (Senior Security Engineer- Account Security • Ap
 ple)\n\nSession Type: SESSION\n\nAll times are in Pacific Daylight Time (P
 DT / UTC-7)
LOCATION:Mandalay Bay H
CLASS:PUBLIC
STATUS:CONFIRMED
