SUMMARY:Let’s Argue About AI Agent Identities (PDT)
DESCRIPTION:There are many strong opinions about AI Agent identities. Shoul
 d AI Agents live in the organization directory right next to humans? Can y
 ou securely give AI Agents access to resources without them having a unify
 ing identity context? How do you treat agents which are all identical memb
 ers of a swarm that would effectively use the same identity? If you’re n
 ot sure where you fall in answering these and many more complex questions 
 about AI Agent identity\, don’t worry. Neither does your speaker. You wi
 ll watch as the speaker debates themself. He will be anonymizing hundreds 
 of conversation had with dozens of organizations at the bleeding edge of t
 hese issues - both on the vendor side making identity & security solutions
  for AI Agents as well as organizations at the bleeding edge of deploying 
 these agents in real world situations. By the end\, the speaker may be mor
 e confused than he started\, but you will know why. You will be armed with
  the pros\, cons\, and confusions of all the AI Agent identity debates of 
 the day.\nTarget Audience & Skill Level: Intermediate to advanced. Many ba
 sics of both AI Agents in enterprise contexts and IAM knowledge will be as
 sumed.\nWhat is New/Novel? For those who have been watching AI Agent ident
 ity from the sidelines\, this will catch them up to the moment on all topi
 cs of the debate.\nKey Takeaways:\nThe current challenges of AI Agent iden
 tityHow identity standards and protocols apply to AI AgentsWhere things li
 ke MCP\, A2A\, and other AI concepts intersect agents & IAMWhy AI Agent id
 entity is neither fully human nor fully non-humanWhat questions should ide
 ntity leaders be asking themselves and their organizations to get the best
  results in AI Agent identity\n\nDetails: https://identiverse.com/idv26/se
 ssion/?idvid=3931790\n\nSpeakers: Jonathan Sander (President • 42 Notion
 s)\n\nSession Type: SESSION\n\nAll times are in Pacific Daylight Time (PDT
  / UTC-7)
LOCATION:Mandalay Bay I
