SUMMARY:Where Are Our Words (PDT)
DESCRIPTION:We in the identity industry are very good at inventing new vert
 icals for products\, but terrible at describing the contexts that underpin
  our ability to describe and evaluate actors within IAM systems. Standards
  work in the IETF seeks to fix this oversight: join Pamela Dingle as she c
 overs the different ways in which metadata discovery\, identifiers for bus
 inesses and agents\, authorization semantics\, and longstanding concepts l
 ike authentication context may converge over time to help us better descri
 be the IAM world around us.\n\nDetails: https://identiverse.com/idv26/sess
 ion/?idvid=3931760\n\nSpeakers: Pamela Dingle (Director of Identity Standa
 rds • Microsoft)\n\nSession Type: SESSION\n\nAll times are in Pacific Da
 ylight Time (PDT / UTC-7)
