SUMMARY:The Foundation for Secure AI Agent Deployment: Governance and Contr
 ol at Scale (PDT)
DESCRIPTION:As organizations move from AI pilots to production\, securing a
 utonomous systems is becoming critical. Most teams lack a dedicated strate
 gy for discovering\, registering\, and governing AI agents as first-class 
 identities.\nIn this session\, we'll share a technical blueprint for secur
 ing AI agent deployments at scale. We'll showcase real-world implementatio
 ns of Cross App Access (XAA) - the new industry standard for securing agen
 t-to-app connections and move beyond basic authentication to address the f
 ull lifecycle of non-human identities.\nAttendees will learn how to:\nEsta
 blish an Identity Control Plane: Register and manage both sanctioned and s
 hadow AI agents within a unified directoryImplement Dynamic Authorization:
  Apply least-privilege principles to autonomous agents chaining actions ac
 ross applicationsMaintain the "Kill Switch": Deploy real-time governance a
 nd automated revocation for rogue agent behaviorUse XAA for Secure Agent C
 onnections: Enable AI agents to act as authorized delegates without manual
  credential handoffs\nWalk away with a practical blueprint for building AI
  transformation on a foundation of digital trust - turning identity into t
 he central control point for the autonomous era.\nSession Presented by:\n\
 nDetails: https://identiverse.com/idv26/session/?idvid=4082871\n\nSpeakers
 : Morgan Reed (Distinguished Strategic Advisor • Okta) | Karan Gondara (
 Manager\, Information Security & Identity • LinkedIn)\n\nSession Type: S
 ESSION\n\nAll times are in Pacific Daylight Time (PDT / UTC-7)
