UID:identiverse-2026-event-3931795@identiverse.com
SEQUENCE:0
DTSTAMP:20260612T220134Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260617T163000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260617T165500
SUMMARY:The Last Mile: Hard-Won Lessons from Netflix's Enterprise Passkey E
 volution (PDT)
DESCRIPTION:Two years after sharing Netflix's initial passkey deployment jo
 urney at Identiverse 2024\, we return with a deep dive into the challenges
  and triumphs in achieving true enterprise-wide adoption. As both our busi
 ness and phishing resistant technologies have evolved\, we encountered com
 plex edge cases that tested the limits of true passwordless authentication
 .\nThis session will share practical insights and data from scaling passke
 y implementation across a diverse (and sometimes hesitant) user base\, nav
 igating changing technology ecosystems\, and managing inconsistent platfor
 m experiences. Through real-world examples and hard lessons learned\, we'l
 l explore practical strategies for tackling the "last mile" of passkey ado
 ption and the realities of maintaining security and usability in an evolvi
 ng business landscape– and share how Netflix's culture with an (almost) 
 no rules rule shaped our approach to achieving comprehensive phishing resi
 stance in a diverse environment.\n\nDetails: https://identiverse.com/idv26
 /session/?idvid=3931795\n\nSpeakers: Sarah Handler (Group Product Manager 
 • Netflix) | Anisha Gupta (Product Manager • Netflix)\n\nSession Type:
  SESSION\n\nAll times are in Pacific Daylight Time (PDT / UTC-7)
LOCATION:Mandalay Bay F
CLASS:PUBLIC
STATUS:CONFIRMED
