BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:identiverse-2026-event-3931770@identiverse.com
SEQUENCE:0
DTSTAMP:20260612T220134Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260617T170500
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260617T173000
SUMMARY:Continuous Authorization – Wrangling the Rule Spaghetti (PDT)
DESCRIPTION:Continuous Authorization lives and dies by its rule set\; are t
 hey doing what you want\, are they doing what you want without burning dow
 n the house\, are they still doing what you want three years later\, after
  multiple people who didn’t understand them have been busy updating them
 .\nWe’ll share some real-world experience of rulesets that have been in 
 place and growing for over 6 years and now exist as the problem that nobod
 y likes\, everyone fears\, but we all can’t live without.\nThrough this 
 session we’ll explore and propose answers to the following questions:\n
 · who is responsible for defining the rules?\n· how do you document them
  successfully?\n· how do you avoid rule spaghetti?\n· how do you know th
 ey’re still appropriate?\n· most importantly: how do you convince the b
 usiness the world will not stop if you remove obsolete rules?\nDefining ru
 les is a group activity as such we’ll cover these questions not just fro
 m the technical implementors perspective but also the product owners\, bus
 iness analysis and the wider business. If you’ve every looked at your cu
 rrent rules and wonders what the hell happened this is the session for you
 !\n\nDetails: https://identiverse.com/idv26/session/?idvid=3931770\n\nSpea
 kers: Paul Heaney (CTO • ProofID) | Darren Scragg (IAM Consultant • Pr
 oofID)\n\nSession Type: SESSION\n\nAll times are in Pacific Daylight Time 
 (PDT / UTC-7)
LOCATION:Mandalay Bay H
CLASS:PUBLIC
