BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:identiverse-2026-event-4092605@identiverse.com
SEQUENCE:0
DTSTAMP:20260612T220134Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260617T170500
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260617T173000
SUMMARY:Who Bought the Bread? Identity and Authentication for AI Agents (PD
 T)
DESCRIPTION:We see the world rapidly shifting from a classic search behavio
 r\, where users find information and act on it themselves\, to learning ho
 w to delegate tasks to AI agents. These digital assistants are quickly evo
 lving from handling simple requests\, like summarizing emails\, to acting 
 as full-service concierges capable of complex\, multi-step tasks like book
 ing entire vacations. But this transition introduces a novel challenge: wh
 en an AI acts\, who is actually acting\, and when they do\, how far can th
 ey go? In this session\, we will explore the complex landscape of identity
  and authentication for AI agents. We will unpack the critical hurdles of 
 this new era\, including:\nDefining and building an agent’s identity\nGi
 ving users more control over apps connected and tasks performed\nExploring
  the topics of agent authentication and authorization\nAttendees will walk
  away with a framework for approaching these emerging challenges\, along w
 ith a high-level overview of how Google is solving for identity\, account 
 linking\, and secure delegation in the age of the AI agents.\nSession Pres
 ented by:\n\nDetails: https://identiverse.com/idv26/session/?idvid=4092605
 \n\nSpeakers: Nafis Zebarjadi (Product Manager • Google) | Ievgeniia Zho
 vtobriukh (Group Product Manager • Google)\n\nSession Type: SESSION\n\nA
 ll times are in Pacific Daylight Time (PDT / UTC-7)
LOCATION:Mandalay Bay D
