SUMMARY:No More Static IDs: Real-Time Assurance in an Age of Deepfakes and 
 Dynamic Compliance (PDT)
DESCRIPTION:As financial institutions explore shifting from physical ID che
 cks to decentralized credentials\, they face a critical gap: how to trust 
 external issuers (DMVs\, Digital Wallets) with the same fidelity as intern
 al controls. This session unveils a unified\, machine-readable metadata fr
 amework designed to bridge the chasm between diverse regional standards (U
 S REAL ID\, EU eIDAS\, AU TDIF) and strict banking regulations (FFIEC\, CI
 P\, AMLA). We will demonstrate how a harmonized schema—utilizing "Crossw
 alk Tables" and dynamic "Revocation Freshness" controls—enables relying 
 parties to programmatically verify credential provenance\, enforce risk-ba
 sed freshness thresholds\, and defend against the rising threat of AI-driv
 en deepfakes in real-time account opening.\n\nDetails: https://identiverse
 .com/idv26/session/?idvid=3931754\n\nSpeakers: Juliana Cafik (Identity Sta
 ndards and Solutions Architect • Independant Expert)\n\nSession Type: SE
 SSION\n\nAll times are in Pacific Daylight Time (PDT / UTC-7)
