SUMMARY:When Identity Fails: Building Resilience and Recovery into Your Ide
 ntity Infrastructure (PDT)
DESCRIPTION:Identity has become Tier 0 infrastructure—essential to every 
 digital interaction. Yet most organizations lack a tested plan for identit
 y continuity when outages or breaches occur. This session explores how to 
 build identity resilience into your architecture\, ensuring business conti
 nuity even when your primary identity provider is compromised.\nWe’ll co
 ver strategies for multi-IDP failover\, immutable identity backups\, and a
 utomated recovery workflows. Drawing from large-scale enterprise transform
 ations\, we’ll share lessons learned from implementing identity continui
 ty in hybrid and multi-cloud environments. Attendees will learn how to ass
 ess their exposure\, design resilient architectures\, and measure identity
  uptime as a business-critical KPI.\nThis session is designed for identity
  architects\, business continuity leaders\, and security professionals. It
  provides a maturity model and decision framework for identity resilience\
 , helping organizations move from reactive recovery to proactive continuit
 y. Attendees will leave equipped to make identity a durable foundation for
  digital trust and operational stability.\n\nDetails: https://identiverse.
 com/idv26/session/?idvid=3931753\n\nSpeakers: Shahan Karim (Principal PM A
 rchitect • Microsoft)\n\nSession Type: SESSION\n\nAll times are in Pacif
 ic Daylight Time (PDT / UTC-7)
LOCATION:Mandalay Bay F
