SUMMARY:Infusing Product Thinking into Identity Teams (PDT)
DESCRIPTION:Many identity teams are composed of brilliant engineers who can
  implement SAML\, LDAP\, or WebAuthn in their sleep\, but they often funct
 ion without a dedicated Product Manager to navigate the "why" behind the "
 what". This lack of product leadership can lead to roadmaps driven solely 
 by technical debt or protocol updates rather than user needs and strategic
  innovation. This talk provides a practical toolkit for engineering-led te
 ams to adopt a product mindset. Drawing from experience in high-stakes env
 ironments\, we will explore how to transition from "maintaining authentica
 tion" to "leading a security product". We’ll discuss how to balance the 
 "unsexy" work—like managing security vulnerabilities and enterprise comp
 liance—with next-generation features like passwordless authentication an
 d non-human identity.\n\nDetails: https://identiverse.com/idv26/session/?i
 dvid=3931663\n\nSpeakers: Hannah Sutor (Product Manager\, Identity and Acc
 ess Management • Netflix)\n\nSession Type: SESSION\n\nAll times are in P
 acific Daylight Time (PDT / UTC-7)
