UID:identiverse-2026-event-3931769@identiverse.com
SEQUENCE:0
DTSTAMP:20260612T220134Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260618T090500
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260618T093000
SUMMARY:Is It Cake? The Crisis of Hidden Crypto and the Path to Agility (PD
 T)
DESCRIPTION:In no other time have we had to question\, to this degree\, wha
 t is real and what is fake. Everyday doubt is pervasive: We see a photo of
  a friend with Tom Cruise and ask ourselves\, ‘Is this real?’ We see a
  hamburger and ask ourselves\, ‘Is it cake?’ On the surface\, everythi
 ng and nothing is cake.\nIn our complex IT infrastructure\, there is no mo
 re of a terrifying question than\, 'Is it cake?' Our systems - from legacy
  applications to acquisition software\, PKIs to databases - can appear sol
 id. But as we take the knife and start to cut\, the truth is revealed: cry
 ptography is often hidden within application code. Within the next five ye
 ars\, quantum computers are thought to have sufficient power to break our 
 current cryptographic systems\, those systems that are central to authenti
 cation\, authorization\, and identity management. When migrating to a quan
 tum resistant identity architecture\, we cannot haphazardly swap our algor
 ithms\; it requires inspecting the cryptographic core of the entire techno
 logy stack.\nThis session will confront how a fractured cryptographic syst
 em poses risk to an enterprise and its customers. We will detail the essen
 tial process of taking inventory of your cryptographic assets—the hardes
 t\, yet most critical\, first step. We'll discuss the need to plan for alg
 orithmic change\, looking beyond today's government-sponsored mandates tow
 ards true quantum readiness. You will leave the session equipped with the 
 tools (knife) to determine if your technology is as agile as it appears (o
 r if it's cake).\n\nDetails: https://identiverse.com/idv26/session/?idvid=
 3931769\n\nSpeakers: Jen Schreiber (Senior II Engineer • CrowdStrike) | 
 Jahan Moreh (Distinguished Security Architect • Workday)\n\nSession Type
 : SESSION\n\nAll times are in Pacific Daylight Time (PDT / UTC-7)
LOCATION:Breakers L
CLASS:PUBLIC
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:OPAQUE
