SUMMARY:Why Britain Hates Digital ID: A Psycho-Historical Tour (PDT)
DESCRIPTION:An overseas digital identity acquaintance of mine recently post
 ed a harmless LinkedIn update: coming to the UK to speak on a panel\, curi
 ous what Brits think about digital ID. Pretty gentle\, nerdy stuff.\nA few
  hours later his comments were a wall of fury\; conspiracies of soul-harve
 sting\, globalist plots. The wrath of British LinkedIn had arrived.\nBrita
 in’s relationship with “papers\, please” is uniquely emotional\, sha
 ped by centuries of uncomfortable encounters between the state and the ind
 ividual. Our resistance is full-throated and patriotic\, even when it make
 s no sense at all.\nIn this talk\, Jaye takes us on an irreverent but insi
 ghtful journey through Britain’s ID angst\, from the second world war to
  Tony Blair's ill-fated 2000s foray\, and the recent resurrection of its d
 igital ghost.\nWe'll see how the coronavirus pandemic calcified our attitu
 des into their current dysfunctional form.\nUnderstanding this cultural op
 erating system is crucial\, because the UK is once again building a nation
 al digital ID. And without reckoning with our past\, we may doom its futur
 e.\nExpect laughs\, uncomfortable truths\, and some truly inscrutable Link
 edIn comments.\n\nDetails: https://identiverse.com/idv26/session/?idvid=39
 31738\n\nSpeakers: Jaye Hackett (Co-founder • Vouchsafe)\n\nSession Type
 : SESSION\n\nAll times are in Pacific Daylight Time (PDT / UTC-7)
LOCATION:Mandalay Bay H
