UID:identiverse-2026-event-3931749@identiverse.com
SEQUENCE:0
DTSTAMP:20260612T220134Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260618T101500
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260618T104000
SUMMARY:From Monthly to Daily: Restoring Trust in Workforce Identity Data W
 hen Applications Won’t Integrate (PDT)
DESCRIPTION:Workforce IAM programs often depend on identity data that is te
 chnically “available\,” but operationally unreliable. In our environme
 nt\, more than 100 applications could not be directly integrated with our 
 IGA platform due to missing APIs\, brittle interfaces\, or turnaround time
 s that made the data unusable for daily identity decisions. As a result\, 
 access data was delivered through a patchwork of manual exports\, screen s
 craping\, PowerShell scripts\, and email or file-share delivery—often on
 ly on a monthly basis.\nThis talk shares our multi-year journey to break t
 hat pattern and restore trust in workforce identity data without waiting f
 or vendors or application owners to modernize. We’ll walk through how we
  identified where human interaction was creating risk\, defined what “go
 od enough” automation looked like for non-integrated applications\, and 
 implemented a repeatable process to convert legacy extracts into timely\, 
 validated data suitable for daily ingestion.\nAttendees will learn how imp
 roving data freshness and reliability directly impacted provisioning accur
 acy\, termination handling\, and overall IAM operational confidence. The s
 ession focuses on practical lessons\, tradeoffs\, and patterns that other 
 IAM teams can apply when perfect integrations are not an option.\n\nDetail
 s: https://identiverse.com/idv26/session/?idvid=3931749\n\nSpeakers: Chris
  Power (Director of IAM Operations • Sallie Mae)\n\nSession Type: SESSIO
 N\n\nAll times are in Pacific Daylight Time (PDT / UTC-7)
LOCATION:Mandalay Bay F
