SUMMARY:Navigating the Hidden Complexities of Identity (PDT)
DESCRIPTION:Identity is often perceived as a simple gateway—a username an
 d a password. However\, identity professionals know the reality is far mor
 e challenging\, characterized by a "deceptive complexity" that lies beneat
 h the surface. Like an iceberg\, what the end user sees is only a fraction
  of the total system. Managing these components\, such as the sprawl of va
 rious access tokens used for automation\, can lead to significant discrupt
 ion if not handled with precision.This session explores how to mitigate th
 is hidden complexity to ensure your solutions provide a seamless and secur
 e experience for end users. We will dive into the PACE Framework\, a strat
 egic approach designed specifically for managing high-impact changes in id
 entity systems. By examining real-world examples\, such as reducing token 
 types at scale\, attendees will learn how to transition from reactive trou
 bleshooting to proactive system management.\n\nDetails: https://identivers
 e.com/idv26/session/?idvid=3931751\n\nSpeakers: Hannah Sutor (Product Mana
 ger\, Identity and Access Management • Netflix)\n\nSession Type: SESSION
 \n\nAll times are in Pacific Daylight Time (PDT / UTC-7)
LOCATION:Breakers J
