UID:identiverse-2026-event-3931757@identiverse.com
SEQUENCE:0
DTSTAMP:20260612T220134Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260618T101500
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260618T104000
SUMMARY:Turning Signals into Trust: The Future of Continuous Identity (PDT)
DESCRIPTION:"There is a great disturbance in the Force." Today’s identity
  systems face a seismic shift—static checkpoints are being replaced by d
 ynamic\, intelligent trust fabrics. As we enter the era of agentic AI and 
 billions of interconnected human and machine identities\, trust must be ad
 aptive\, collaborative\, and continuous.If identity is the Force\, SSF is 
 what binds it. But to face today’s threats\, SSF must move from a quiet 
 tremor to an active shield\, orchestrating trust across the galaxy.In this
  session\, we explore the leap from basic signaling to a Living Trust Fabr
 ic. We will dive into real-world use cases—ranging from continuous provi
 sioning and ATO prevention to machine identity assurance—while unveiling
  the roadmap for the next generation of SSF.Attendees will leave with:\nA 
 Blueprint for Bi-Directional Trust: Understand how Transceivers move SSF t
 o enable true bi-directional signal orchestration.\nA Framework for Accoun
 tability: Learn how to use Action Receipts to maintain continuous governan
 ce (GRC) and auditability for autonomous agents.\nThe Roadmap to a Dynamic
  Trust Fabric: Discover how to transition from passive signaling to an act
 ive\, autonomous enforcement engine capable of responding to risks at scal
 e.\nJoin us to see how Shared Signals are becoming the universal language 
 of trust—bringing balance to the identity ecosystem and shaping the next
  generation of secure\, interoperable\, and visionary digital identity.\n\
 nDetails: https://identiverse.com/idv26/session/?idvid=3931757\n\nSpeakers
 : Atul Tulshibagwale (Senior Director\, Continuous Identity Strategy • C
 rowdStrike) | Mike Kiser (Director of Strategy and Standards • SailPoint
 ) | Sean O'Dell (Distinguished Engineer\, Identity & Security • CVS Heal
 th)\n\nSession Type: SESSION\n\nAll times are in Pacific Daylight Time (PD
 T / UTC-7)
LOCATION:Mandalay Bay I
CLASS:PUBLIC
