SUMMARY:Bidirectional OAuth 2.0 / Open ID Connect (PDT)
DESCRIPTION:OAuth 2.0 / OpenID Connect have been one of the most fundamenta
 l frameworks with applications in social logins and data sharing. The curr
 ent standard OAuth framework is designed for unidirectional data sharing\,
  with one of the partners being the relying party. Modern applications nee
 d data sharing bidirectionally between partners. We present a framework bu
 ilt on top of the current OAuth 2.0 / OpenID Connect frameworks\, which al
 lows for bidirectional user authorization and subsequent data sharing.\n\n
 Details: https://identiverse.com/idv26/session/?idvid=3931778\n\nSpeakers:
  Dhandapany Venkatasubramanian (Standards Architect\, Identity • PayPal 
 Inc)\n\nSession Type: SESSION\n\nAll times are in Pacific Daylight Time (P
 DT / UTC-7)
