SUMMARY:100 Years of Identity... You’d Think We’d Be Better at This (PD
 T)
DESCRIPTION:Our industry isn’t defined by some ancient history but instea
 d is a dynamic and emergent collection of lived experience\, trial and err
 or\, good ideas\, and “what were they thinking” moments. …something 
 people just like you may have experienced and continue to experience. Tech
 nical standards\, industry organizations\, and trends come and go\; their 
 history and their future is best understood through the people who partici
 pated in them and even caused them to happen. With over 100 years of indus
 try experience on stage\, this panel will discuss our shared history\, bes
 t guesses as to the industry’s direction\, and what excites them about t
 he future of our practice.\nAttendees will:\nGain lessons on responding to
  challenges and opportunities through the shared experiences of the paneli
 sts\nLearn the “why” behind many commonly used standards and practices
 \, whether loved or un-\nBecome emboldened in realizing the future of iden
 tity is theirs\, individually\, to shape\n\nDetails: https://identiverse.c
 om/idv26/session/?idvid=3931662\n\nSpeakers: Eve Maler (President/Founder 
 • Venn Factory) | Andrew Cameron (Distinguished Engineer\, IAM • GM) |
  Pamela Dingle (Director of Identity Standards • Microsoft) | Ian Glazer
  (Head of Continuous Identity Product Strategy • CrowdStrike)\n\nSession
  Type: KEYNOTE\n\nAll times are in Pacific Daylight Time (PDT / UTC-7)
